{META_DATA}: BLACK SCREEN
{META_DATA}: SUPER: New Line Cinema Presents
{META_DATA}: SUPER: A Wingnut Films Production
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLACK CONTINUES... ELVISH SINGING....A WOMAN'S VOICE IS whispering, tinged with SADNESS and REGRET:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: subtitled)
{DIALOGUE}: "I amar prestar sen: han mathon ne nen, han mathon ne chae...a han noston ned wilith."
{META_DATA}: (English:)
{DIALOGUE}: The world is changed: I feel it in the water, I feel it in the earth, I smell it in the air...Much that once was is lost, for none now live who remember it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUPER: THE LORD OF THE RINGS
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PROLOGUE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: FLICKERING FIRELIGHT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The NOLDORIN FORGE in EREGION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOLTEN GOLD POURS from the lip of an IRON LADLE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: It began with the forging of the Great Rings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: THREE RINGS, each set with a single GEM, are received by the HIGH ELVES-GALADRIEL, GIL-GALAD and CIRDAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Three were given to the Elves, immortal, wisest...fairest of all beings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: SEVEN RINGS held aloft in triumph by the DWARF LORDS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Seven to the Dwarf Lords, great miners and craftsmen of the mountain halls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: NINE RINGS clutched tightly by the KINGS OF MEN...as if holding-close a precious secret.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: And Nine...nine rings were gifted to the race of Men who, above all else, desire power.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: For within these rings was bound the strength and will to govern each race.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But they were all of them deceived.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP: An ancient PARCHMENT MAP of MIDDLE EARTH...moving slowly across the MAP as if drawn by an unseen force the CAMERA closes in on a PLACE NAME...MORDOR.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...for another ring was made.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TEASING SHOTS: SAURON forging the ONE RING in the CHAMBERS of SAMMATH NAUR.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: In the land of Mordor, in the fires of Mount Doom, the Dark Lord Sauron forged in secret a Master Ring to control all others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: The ONE RING reflecting FIERY LAVA!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIRE WRITING emerges on the plain BAND OF GOLD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and into this Ring he poured his cruelty, his malice and his will to dominate all life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: THE ONE RING falls through SPACE and into flames...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: One Ring to rule them all...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: A GREAT SHADOW falls across the MAP...closing in around the realm of GONDOR...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: SCREAMING VILLAGERS, MEN, WOMEN, AND CHILDREN, RUN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: from their homes, pursued by ARMIES OF HIDEOUS ORCS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: One by one the Free lands of Middle earth fell to the power of the ring.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But there were some...who resisted.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 3.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP: ISILDUR, son of the KING OF GONDOR, leads an ARMY ACROSS the PLAINS OF DAGORLAD...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: A last alliance of Men and Elves marched against the armies of Mordor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: On the slopes of Mount Doom they fought for the freedom of Middle- Earth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TEASING SHOTS: THE BATTLE OF DAGORLAD...THE ELF LORD, ELROND,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: commands rank after rank of ELVEN ARCHERS...ORCS RETREATING before the ARMY of the LAST ALLIANCE...ELENDIL holds aloft the great sword....NARSIL!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Victory was near!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGES: THE HUGE, DARK FIGURE OF SARURON, bearing the ONE RING on his finger, looms over the field of battle...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But the power of the Ring could not be undone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: SAURON lays waste to the armies of the LAST ALLIANCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With desperate courage, ELENDIL leads a charge...THE BLACK MACE OF SAURON LASHES OUT!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: ELENDIL'S body falls like a crumpled rag doll... IMAGE: ISILDUR cradles the body of his father in his arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SHADOW OF SAURON falls over him...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It was in this moment.
{DIALOGUE}: when all hope had faded, that Isildur, son of the king, took up his father's sword.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ISILDUR snatches up the BROKEN BLADE OF NARSIL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BLADE severs SAURON'S FINGERS... AND THE ONE RING FLIES from his body.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron, the enemy of the Free Peoples of Middle Earth, was defeated.
{DIALOGUE}: SAURON'S ARMOR clatters to the ground.
{DIALOGUE}: His body
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GONE....VAPORIZED!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ISILDUR picks up the SEVERED FINGER and removes the ONE RING...transfixed!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The Ring passed to Isildur...who had this one chance to destroy evil forever.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 4.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: GLADDEN FIELD...ISILDUR leads a small column of men through DARKENING WOODS...the ONE RING glinting on a CHAIN around his neck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But the hearts of Men are easily corrupted.
{DIALOGUE}: And the Ring of Power has a will of its own.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARROWS FLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are ambushed by ORCS...ISILDUR SCREAMS!
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP: ISILDUR MATERIALIZES UNDER WATER...as THE RING slips slowly from his finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ripples of LIGHT play across ISILDUR'S PALE FACE...he is DEAD.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It betrayed Isildur to his death.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: THE RING falls through the MURKY WATERS of the RIVER ANDUIN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: And some things that should not have been forgotten...were lost.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: History became legend...legend became myth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP: The waters of the ANDUIN RIVER lie dark and undisturbed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: And for two and a half thousand years the Ring passed out of all knowledge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: SILT SWIRLS...A THIN WHITE HAND reaches down...grasping the RING...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Until, when chance came, it ensnared a new bearer!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: THE THIN WHITE HAND opens to reveal one ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOLLUM (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: My Precious...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 5.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: MIST SHROUDED MOUNTAINS...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: The Ring came to the creature Gollum, who took it deep into the tunnels of the Misty Mountains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: THE GLOOM of a MOUNTAIN CAVERN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a MURKY POOL of WATER...in the DARKNESS the SHADOWY OUTLINE of an EMACIATED FIGURE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: And there, it consumed him.
{DIALOGUE}: A RASPY VOICE mutters in the half light...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOLLUM
{DIALOGUE}: It came to me.
{DIALOGUE}: My own.
{DIALOGUE}: My love...
{META_DATA}: (ecstatic whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: My preciousness.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: The Ring brought to Gollum unnatural long life.
{DIALOGUE}: For five hundred years it poisoned his mind.
{DIALOGUE}: And in the gloom of Gollum's cave...
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It waited.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP: Bathed in COLD MOONLIGHT, the WORLD lies DARK and STILL...the unsettled quiet before the storm...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Darkness crept back into the forests of the world.
{DIALOGUE}: Rumor grew of a Shadow in the East...whispers of a nameless fear.
{DIALOGUE}: And the Ring of Power perceived...its time had now come.
{DIALOGUE}: It abandoned Gollum.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SLOW MOTION: unseen by its KEEPER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE RING falls to the MUDDY FLOOR of a MOUNTAIN TUNNEL...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But something happened then the Ring did not intend...
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: FUMBLING in the dark, a SMALL HAND closes over the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 6.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: It was picked up by the most unlikely creature imaginable...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: What's this?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A YOUNGISH LOOKING BILBO BAGGINS peers down at what lies in his hand...PERPLEXED by what he has found.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: A Hobbit....Bilbo Baggins of the Shire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{META_DATA}: (surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: A Ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A VOICE SCREAMS...ITS ANGUISH RINGING through the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLD, DANK TUNNELS...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOLLUM (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Lost!
{DIALOGUE}: Lost!
{DIALOGUE}: My Precious is lost!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frightened Bilbo quickly POCKETS the ONE RING and hurries on.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: THE CAMERA SOARS AWAY FROM THE MOUNTAINS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING
