{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHITE PEAKS RECEDING INTO THE SHROUD OF MIST
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: For the time will soon come when Hobbits will shape the fortunes of all.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBITON WOODS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: TWO HOBBIT FEET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: resting on a small rock...rising out of the LONG, OVERGROWN GRASSES SUPER: THE FELLOWSHIP OF THE RING SUPER: THE SHIRE....60 YEARS LATER CAMERA TRACKS TO: a Figure lies beneath the dappled sunlight of an old tree.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 7.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: White flowers are scattered among the Well seeded grasses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An idyllic setting at the end of a long hot summer... the figure is reading a book.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE SOUNDTRACK: In the distance, growing louder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: over the Gentle clip clop of an approaching cart and horse can be heard the HUMMING OF A DEEP VOICE to the tune of "The Road Goes Ever On and On..."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The figure in the grass sits up...looking straight at camera is a handsome young HOBBIT, with dark curly hair and deep blue eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is FRODO BAGGINS...his EYES alight with EXCITEMENT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tossing away the long stem of grass in his mouth, Frodo runs off.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SHIRE LANE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cart rattles along a leafy lane, driven by a stooped figure in Grey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INTERCUT WITH; SHOTS OF FRODO RUNNING... CAREERING DOWN A
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HILL. . .JUMPING OVER LOGS... DODGING TREE BRANCHES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shambling OLD PONY snorts and rears as... SUDDENLY FRODO appears on a bank above the cart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You're late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: GANDALF glowers at the young Hobbit...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: A Wizard is never late, Frodo Baggins, nor is he early.
{DIALOGUE}: He arrives precisely when he means to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look at each other a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: then both start laughing as FRODO'S face breaks into a smile and he leaps on to the front seat of the cart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: It's wonderful to see you, Gandalf!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to Gandalf, we see how small Hobbits are...Frodo is 3 foot 6 inches tall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't think I'd miss your Uncle Bilbo's birthday?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 8.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBITON FIELDS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: The cart rattles past a FIELD LUPIN being tended by
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOBBITS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What news of the outside world?
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me everything!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks down at Frodo, a twinkle in his eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: What, everything?
{DIALOGUE}: Far too eager and curious for a Hobbit.
{DIALOGUE}: Most unnatural...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: The cart rattles over a Stone bridge towards a Busy Hobbit Marketplace.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, what can I tell you?
{DIALOGUE}: Life in the wide world goes on much as if it has past age.
{DIALOGUE}: Full of its own comings and goings, scarcely even aware of the existence of Hobbits...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Gandalf as he surveys the peaceful scene before him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...for which I am very thankful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hobbits look up exclaiming in wonder and excitement as the cart bearing Gandalf and Frodo rolls past the Green Dragon Inn...towards... Wide on: The party field.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Where scOrcs of Hobbits are busy preparing for the big night.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, the long expected party.
{DIALOGUE}: So, how is the old rascal?
{DIALOGUE}: I hear it's going to be a Party of Special Magnificence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You know Bilbo...he's got he whole place in an uproar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, well...that should please him.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 9.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Half the Shire's been invited...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Good gracious, me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: He's up to something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, really?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo shoots a knowing look, as Gandalf averts his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Alright then.
{DIALOGUE}: keep your secrets.
{DIALOGUE}: Before you came along we Bagginses were very well thought of.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Indeed?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Never had any adventures or did anything unexpected.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: If you're referring to the incident with the Dragon...I was barely involved...all I did was give your Uncle a little nudge out the door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever you did...you've been officially labelled as a Disturber of the Peace.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, really?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ODO PROUDFOOT looks up as the Cart passes by, deeply suspicious.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBITON -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANE UP:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the cart rattles into the small village of Hobbiton...a quaint rustic settlement, nestled amongst rolling green hills and large trees.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 10.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hobbits live in Hobbit Holes: neat burrows dug into the grassy hillside, with round doors and cute front gardens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Excited children, chasing after the cart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf ignOrcs the children's cries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The children stand deflated, watching Gandalf disappear up the lane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At that moment: spinning balls of bright color suddenly leap out of the cart, fizzing over the heads of the delighted children.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf smiling to himself, well pleased with his joke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ODO PROUDFOOT is unable to suppress a chuckle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo stands up in the cart as Gandalf reigns in the horse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf... I'm glad you're back.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo leaps expertly from the cart.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: So am I, dear boy...so am I
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAG END -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: GANDALF'S CART pulls up outside the gate to BAG END...a particularly fine example of a Hobbit hole, with a large round front door set into a grassy hillside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a sign on the gate which reads: "NO ADMITTANCE EXCEPT ON PARTY BUSINESS."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf strides up to the garden path of Bag End.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his staff and raps on the front door...a voice calls out:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: No, thank you!
{DIALOGUE}: We don't want any more visitors, well wishers, or distant relations.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: And what about very old friends?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly the door opens and BILBO BAGGINS stands before him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is a HOBBIT OF INDERTIMINATE AGE, with a mischievous Twinkle in his eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wearing a dashing brocade waist coat, he looks every inch the eccentric gentleman.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 11.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo Baggins!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: My dear Gandalf!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf drops to his knee to embrace his old friend.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: It's good to see you.
{DIALOGUE}: One hundred and eleven years old, who would believe it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at him more keenly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You haven't aged a day!
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf and Bilbo laugh together and enter Bag End.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, come in!
{DIALOGUE}: Welcome, welcome!!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo leads Gandalf into Bag End...cozy and cluttered with souvenirs of Bilbo's travels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf has to stoop to avoid hitting his head on the low ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo hangs up Gandalf's hat on a peg and trots off down the hall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{META_DATA}: (Calling)
{DIALOGUE}: Tea?
{DIALOGUE}: Or maybe something stronger... I've a few bottles of the Old Winyard left, 1296...a very good year, almost as old as I am.
{DIALOGUE}: It was laid down by my father.
{DIALOGUE}: What say we open one, eh?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo disappears into the kitchen as Gandalf looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: enjoying the familiarity of Bag End...he turns, knocking his head on the light and then walking into the wooden beam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He groans.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (O.S.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I was expecting you some time last week.
{DIALOGUE}: Not that it matters, you come and go as you please, always have done, always will.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 12.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (O.S.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You've caught me a bit unprepared, I'm afraid...we've only got cold chicken, bit of pickle, some cheese here...ooh, no, that might be a little risky...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf stops in front of a framed map, charred in one corner...it is Thorin's map of the Lonely Mountain, Gandalf smiles to himself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Er, we've got raspberry jam and apple tart...got some custard somewhere.
{DIALOGUE}: Not much for Afters, I'm afraid.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh no...we're alright...I've just found some sponge cake.
{DIALOGUE}: Nice little snack.
{DIALOGUE}: Hope it's enough.
{META_DATA}: (comes into view)
{DIALOGUE}: I could do you some eggs if you like?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo jumps, a half eaten pork pie in his hand, as Gandalf mysteriously appears behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Just tea, thank you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Oh.
{DIALOGUE}: right.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't mind if...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, not at all.
{DIALOGUE}: Go ahead.
{DIALOGUE}: A sudden loud knock on the front door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. SACKVILLE BAGGINS (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo Baggins, you open this door.
{DIALOGUE}: I know you're in there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf watches, amused as Bilbo tries to hide.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I've got to get away from these confounded relatives, hanging on the bell all day, never giving me a moment's peace.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to see mountains again...mountains, Gandalf... and then find somewhere quiet where I can finish my book...Oh, Tea!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: So, you mean to go through with your plan, then?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 13.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, yes...it's all inhand.
{DIALOGUE}: All the arrangements are made.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo suspects something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: 'Course he does, he's a Baggins...not some block headed Bracegirdle from Hardbottle!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You will tell him, won't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: He's very fond of you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{DIALOGUE}: He'd probably come with me if I asked him.
{DIALOGUE}: I think, in his heart, Frodo's still in love with the Shire, the woods and the fields... little rivers.
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo stands gazing out of the kitchen window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I am old, Gandalf... Bilbo looks at Gandalf sadly...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I know I don't look it, but I'm beginning to feel it in my heart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo's fingers close around his waistcoat pocket...gripping a small, unseen object.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I feel thin...sort of stretched, like butter scraped over too much bread.
{DIALOGUE}: I need a holiday...a very long holiday and I don't expect I shall return...in fact, I mean not to.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 14.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END -- EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf and Bilbo are sitting on the Bag End porch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Below them, final preparations are being made on the Party field.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo strikes a match and lights his pipe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Old Toby, the finest weed in Southfarthing!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo blows a perfect smoke ring and watches it rise into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tiny sailing ship with masts and sails glides through the Center of Bilbo's smoke ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Ohhhh,
{META_DATA}: (smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf my old friend...this will be a night to remember!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PARTY FIELD, HOBBITON -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FIREWORK explodes into the night sky high above Hobbiton...in the shape of a great green tree with unfolding branches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TILT DOWN: with glowing flowers as they rain down from the branches...evaporating just above the up turned faces of the delighted party-goers 144 Hobbits, feasting and drinking Carts of beer and wine are scattered about, and the tables are piled high with steaming scones and savories.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf hurries about, lighting fireworks with a blue spark that dances magically from his staff... Bilbo is greeting visitors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo and SAM sit at a table drinking ale...Frodo notices Sam's eyes keep flicking to another pretty Hobbit, Rosie Cotton, sitting some distance away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Go on, Sam, ask Rosie for a dance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (horrified)
{DIALOGUE}: I think I'll just have myself another ale.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, no you don't.
{DIALOGUE}: Go on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam goes to drain his glass... suddenly it is snatched out of his hands as Frodo thrusts him into the middle of a passing throng of dancers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 15.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SAM'S HORRIFIED FACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he is Swept away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo laughs and finishes Sam's beer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf as he sets alight a particularly spectacular firework that draws gasps of admiration from the party guests.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Bilbo is relating stories of his adventure to a group of young hobbit children.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{META_DATA}: (melodramatic)
{DIALOGUE}: So, there I was...at the mercy of three monstrous trolls...Have you ever heard of a troll?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know what a Troll is?
{DIALOGUE}: Great big nasty twenty foot high smelly things.
{DIALOGUE}: and they're arguing...arguing about how they were going to cook us!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: A LITTLE HOBBIT GIRL'S
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: upturned face...her eyes growing larger and larger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Whether it be turned on a spit or minced in a pie or whether they were going to sit on us one by one and squash us into jelly!
{DIALOGUE}: But they spent so long arguing the whether-to's and why-for's that the sun's first light crept over the top of the trees...and turned them all to stone!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STUNNED GASPS from his young Audience greet his astonishing feat!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: MERRY AND PIPPIN, two mischievous Young Hobbits in their late teens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin scrambles on to the back of Gandalf's wagon, snatching up a small firework
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (urgent whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: No, no.
{DIALOGUE}: the big one...the big one!
{DIALOGUE}: Pippin grabs a huge rocket.
{DIALOGUE}: CLOSE ON: FIREWORK FUSE crackles with flame!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry is holding out the big rocket...he looks aghast at the fizzing fuse that Pippin has just lit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (worried whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: You're supposed to stick it in the ground!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 16.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: It is in the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry fearfully tosses the Rocket to Pippin!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fuse sizzles angrily.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Outside!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: It was your idea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin attempts to throw the fizzing rocket back to Merry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHOOSH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two hobbits are suddenly blown off their feet in a shower of sparks as the rocket blasts off with frightening power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ROCKET ZOOMS over the Party.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It suddenly bursts apart, forming the shape of a great red golden Dragon!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fire gushes from its nostrils as it turns back and Flies low towards the startled crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo watches the Fireworks Dragon with alarm...but Bilbo is oblivious to the Panicking crowd and impending danger!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo!
{DIALOGUE}: Watch out for the dragon!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Dragon?
{DIALOGUE}: Nonsense...hasn1t been a dragon in these parts for a thousand years!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he hurriedly pulls Bilbo to the ground, just as the dragon roars a few feet above their heads like a flaming express train!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hobbits dive to the ground, tables overturn, tents collapse, food flies everywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fireworks dragon turns a somersault and explodes over the hills with a deafening bang!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This gets the biggest Cheer of the night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: MERRY AND PIPPIN,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: clothes and hair smoking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: That was good!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get another one!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LARGE HANDS suddenly clamp down on Merry and Pippin's ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Low angle: Gandalf looking DOWN STERNLY!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 17.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Meridoc Brandybuck and Peregrin Took...I might have known!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MERRY AND PIPPIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Are leaning over a barrel, washing dishes in soapy water...with Gandalf sitting nearby, smoking his pipe and sipping an ale.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cries of "SPEECH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SPEECH" erupt from the party.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo stepping on a stool...he bows in gratitude at the applause.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Speech!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{META_DATA}: (clearing throat)
{DIALOGUE}: My dear Bagginses, and Boffins, tooks and Brandybucks...Grubbs, Chubbs, Hornblowers, Bolgers, Bracegirdles and Proudfoots...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: A HOBBIT WITH PARTICULARLY BIG FEET
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ODO PROUDFOOT
{DIALOGUE}: Proudfeet!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Today is my one hundred and eleventh birthday.
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, and alas...Eleventy- one years is far too short a time to live among such excellent and admirable Hobbits!
{DIALOGUE}: Tremendous outburst of approval!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know half of you half as well as I should like; and I like less than half of you as well as well as you deserve.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SCATTERED CLAPPING as the guests try to work out if that was a compliment or not.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO AND GANDALF smiling to themselves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Bilbo...a strange hum seems to fill his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bead of sweat rolls down his brow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo's hand pulls something out of his waistcoat pocket and holds it behind his back.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 18.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I have.
{DIALOGUE}: things to do and I have put this off for far too long... CLOSE ON: BILBO'S knuckles turn white as he tightens his grip on the small object behind his back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I regret to announce, this is the end.
{DIALOGUE}: I am going now.
{DIALOGUE}: I bid you all a very fond farewell!!
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo looks across at Frodo, hesitates... then...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo instantly vanishes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The party explodes into an uproar... the crowd leaps to its feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: staring at the empty stool in disbelief.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAG END -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The party is still in an excited uproar... some 50 yards away as we pan across a moonlit lane to the front door of Bag End.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Door opens, pulled by an invisible hand.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door quietly closes...Bilbo materializes as he pulls a plain gold ring off his finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo laughs as he tosses the ring in the air, then places it in his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo emerges from the passage, carrying a walking stick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finds Gandalf looming over him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I suppose you think that was terribly clever?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Gandalf!
{DIALOGUE}: Did you see their faces?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 19.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: There are many magic rings in the world, Bilbo Baggins, and none of them should be used lightly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: It was just a bit of fun.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, you're probably right as usual.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You will keep an eye on Frodo, won't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: I'm leaving everything to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: What about this ring of yours?
{DIALOGUE}: Is that staying too?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Bilbo...he gives Gandalf a look and nods toward the mantelpiece.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, yes, it's in an envelope...over there on the mantelpiece.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf frowns at the empty mantelpiece...Bilbo suddenly feels his waistcoat with a look of guilty surprise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: No, wait.
{DIALOGUE}: It's here in my pocket.
{DIALOGUE}: Isn't that...isn't' that odd now?
{DIALOGUE}: Yet, after all, why not?
{DIALOGUE}: Why shouldn't I keep it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I think you should leave the Ring behind, Bilbo.
{DIALOGUE}: Is that so hard?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Well, no...and yes.
{DIALOGUE}: Now it comes to it, I don't feel like parting with it.
{DIALOGUE}: It's mine.
{DIALOGUE}: I found it.
{DIALOGUE}: It came to me!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: GANDALF LOOKS DOWN AT BILBO WITH RISING CONCERN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: There's no need to get angry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Well, if I'm angry, it's your fault!
{DIALOGUE}: It's mine.
{DIALOGUE}: My own, my precious.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 20.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Precious?
{DIALOGUE}: It's been called that before, but not by you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: So?
{DIALOGUE}: What business is it of yours what I do with my own things?
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo's voice, shape and manner have suddenly changed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I think you've had that ring quite long enough.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: You want it for yourself!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf rises to his full height, his eyes flash, his shadow suddenly seems to fill the room
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo Baggins do not take me for some conjurer of cheap tricks!
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo cowers from Gandalf, disarmed by his power...a frightened Hobbit.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf's expression softens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I am not trying to rob you.
{DIALOGUE}: I am trying to help you.
{DIALOGUE}: Sobbing, Bilbo runs to Gandalf and hugs him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: All you long years we've been friends...trust me as you once did.
{DIALOGUE}: Let it go!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: You're right, Gandalf...the ring must go to Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo lifts his knapsack and heads for the front door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It's late, the road is long... yes, it is time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Hmmm?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 21.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: The ring is still in your pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo hesitates...reaches into his pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Bilbo pulls out the ring...he stares at it in his palm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With all his will power, Bilbo allows the ring to slowly slide off his palm and drop to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: The tiny ring lands with a heavy thud on the wooden floor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAG END -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo staggering out of Bag end...he braces himself in the night air, Pale and Trembling, as if his loss of the ring has weakened him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf steps up behind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: I've thought up and ending for my book..."And he lived happily ever after to the end of his days."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sure you will, my dear friend.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye, Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye Bilbo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo walks away from Bag End, disappearing into the night, softly singing: "The Road goes on and on."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: Until our next meeting.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: THE RING...Glinting on the floor...Gandalf circles around it, a Puzzled look on his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf slowly reaches for the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His fingers barely touch the ring...the creepy Hum rises on the soundtrack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is sitting in front of the fire, with his pipe...staring into the flickering flames.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 22.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: It's mine, my own, my precious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: Riddles in the dark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo!
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo rushes into Bag End...he stops and picks up the ring at his feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf continues staring into the fire, as if locked in thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: My precious...precious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: He's gone, hasn't he?
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo steps into the living room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: He talked for so long about leaving...I didn't think he'd really do it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (mutters to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: ...my own.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf turns...his eyes locking onto the ring in Frodo's fingers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo's ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf sorts hurriedly through Bilbo's papers...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: He's gone to stay with the Elves.
{DIALOGUE}: He's left you Bag End...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf holds out the envelope...Frodo drops the ring into it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...along with all his possessions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandolf seals the envelope with wax.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hands it to Frodo.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 23.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The ring is yours now.
{DIALOGUE}: But it somewhere out of sight.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf rises hurriedly and starts to gather his things.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I have some things I must see to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What things?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Questions.
{DIALOGUE}: Questions that need answering.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You've only just arrived!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't understand...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is already at the door, he turns to Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Neither do I. Keep it secret, keep it safe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf hurries out the door...leaving FRODO standing alone in the Bag End.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: THE ENVELOPE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera pushes in...the hum of the ring comes up on the soundtrack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera pushes through the white paper to the ring...beneath the hum the whispered murmur of BLACK SPEECH can be heard.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BARAD-DUR -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The jagged ruins of" BARAD-DUR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DARK TOWER!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TEASING IMAGES: THE HUGE DARK TOWER OF BARAD-DUR is being rebuilt!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thousands of ORCS crawl over the surface, hauling stone and iron up the towering heights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: MOUNT DOOM...A HUGE, BILLOWING CLOUD OF BLACK FILTH
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: grows and spreads across the red streaked sky...casting a shadowy pall over the nightmarish landscape.
