{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 24.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOLLUM (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Baggins!
{DIALOGUE}: Shire!!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MINAS MORGUL -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NINE BLACK RIDERS burst out of Minas Morgul and charge toward Camera.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE WEST ROAD, GONDOR -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: A LONE HORSEMAN gallops to the crest of a hill on the west road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The main highway south to Minas Tirith...he looks toward the saw toothed mountains of Mordor... ...seeping out across the blood red sky, his face grave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spurs his horse on.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CITADEL, MINAS TIRITH -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: GANDALF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: making is way down into the lower depths of the Citidel.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CITADEL CHAMBER, MINAS TIRITH -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Pages flipping as Gandalf searches ancient scrolls and books placed high on a wooden table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes settle on one old parchment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He murmurs hurriedly to himself, reading.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (reading)
{DIALOGUE}: The year 3434 of the Second Age...here follows the account of Isildur, High King of Gondor, and the finding of the ring of power.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ISILDUR, TRIUMPHANT, REACHES FOR THE ONE RING, HIS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: EYES FIXATED ON IT.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (reading)
{DIALOGUE}: It has come to me...the ring of power!
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 25.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It shall be an heirloom of my Kingdom...all those who follow in my bloodline shall be bound to its fate, for I will risk no hurt to the
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ring...it is precious to me, though I buy it with great pain...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ELVISH LETTERING MARKS ON THE FADED OLD DOCUMENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN GANDALF'S HAND.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (reading)
{DIALOGUE}: The marking upon the band begin to fade...the writing which at first was as clear as red flame, has all but disappeared...a secret now that only fire can tell...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBIT FARMHOUSE -- EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FARMER MAGGOT is chopping wood in his garden CLOSE ON: SNORTING HORSE NOSTRILS...as the shadow of a black rider looms over a Hobbit House.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrified, FARMER MAGGOT cowers in his doorway...FANG, his dog, Whimpers and backs away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BLACK RIDER
{META_DATA}: (hissing)
{DIALOGUE}: Shire?
{DIALOGUE}: Baggins?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FARMER MAGGOT
{META_DATA}: (terrified)
{DIALOGUE}: There's no Bagginses around here!
{DIALOGUE}: They are all up in Hobbiton...that way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BLACK RIDER GALLOPS AWAY AT SPEED
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GREEN DRAGON INN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: ROSIE COTTON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: bids the last of the Patron's "Goodnight"...Sam meets her eyes for a moment as he and Frodo leave the inn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 26.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAG END -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: FRODO FAREWELLS SAM outside Bag End, and heads towards the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Creepy POV from inside Bag end: Frodo coming up the path.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END HALLWAY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO enters Bag End...he immediately Pauses, sensing that something is amiss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All is quiet...Frodo peers uneasily into the darkened living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A large figure looms out of the shadows, reaching for Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo lets out a startled cry, pulls himself free and spins around to face his Assailant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf steps into a shaft of moonlight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paranoia blazes in his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His clothes are dirty and ragged from much traveling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hair and beard much longer an unkempt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (urgent whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Is it secret?
{DIALOGUE}: Is it safe?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo pulls the envelope out of an old chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf, suspicious, Alert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without a word, Gandalf takes the envelope and tosses it into the fireplace!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (bewildered)
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flames instantly consume the envelope...revealing the ring, as it sinks into the red hot embers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf reaches into the fire with a pair of tongs...he lifts the ring out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Hold out your hand, Frodo...it is quite cool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf drops the ring into Frodo's hand...he reacts to its weight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: What can you see?
{DIALOGUE}: Can you see anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing...there's nothing.
{DIALOGUE}: Wait...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 27.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: The Gold Band of the ring as fiery letters begin to appear...a tiny inscription glows red...as if burning from within.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: ...these are markings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: GANDALF...STILL...TENSE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRO DO
{DIALOGUE}: It's some form of Elvish...I can't read it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (ominous)
{DIALOGUE}: There are few who can...the language is that of Mordor, which I will not utter here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mordor?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: GANDALF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the common tongue it says, "One ring to rule them all, One ring to find them, One ring to bring them all, and in the darkness bind them."
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END KITCHEN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: The ring lies on Frodo's simple kitchen table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: This is the one ring forged by the dark lord, Sauron, in the fires of Mt Doom...taken by Isildur from the hand of Sauron himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO...STUNNED
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (quiet realization)
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo found it...in Gollom's cave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: For sixty years the ring lay quiet in Bilbo's keeping, prolonging his life, delaying old age...but no longer, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: Evil is stirring in Mordor.
{DIALOGUE}: The ring has awoken.
{DIALOGUE}: It has heard its master's call.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 28.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: AT THAT MOMENT: A FLEETING, LOW WHISPER of BLACK SPEECH
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: emanates from the Ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks at Gandalf, each knowing the other has heard it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: But he was destroyed...Sauron was destroyed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: THE RING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: lies between them on the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: The spirit of Sauron has endured.
{DIALOGUE}: His life force is bound to the ring and the ring survived.
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron has returned.
{DIALOGUE}: His Orcs have multiplied...his fortress of Barad- dur is rebuilt in the land of Mordor.
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron needs only this ring to cover all the lands in the second darkness.
{DIALOGUE}: He is seeking it, seeking it, all his thought is bent on it.
{DIALOGUE}: For the ring yearns, above all else, to return to the hand of its master: they are one, the ring and the dark lord.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo, he must never find out.
{DIALOGUE}: SUDDENLY Frodo scoops up the Ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Alright!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hurriedly entering the living room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (thinking fast)
{DIALOGUE}: We put it away, we keep it hidden!
{DIALOGUE}: We never speak of it again.
{DIALOGUE}: No one know it's here, do they?
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf shifts uncomfortably.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Do they, Gandalf?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at Frodo, sadly...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 29.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: There is one other who knew that Bilbo had the Ring.
{DIALOGUE}: I looked everywhere for the creature Gollum, but the enemy found him first.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BARAD-DUR -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: A teasing Glimpse of Gollum being tortured by the Orcs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wretched creature screams in pain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know how long they tortured him...but amidst the endless screams and inane babble, they discerned two words.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOLLUM
{META_DATA}: (screaming)
{DIALOGUE}: S..
{DIALOGUE}: Shire!
{DIALOGUE}: Baggins!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO'S HORRIFIED FACE!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Shire!
{DIALOGUE}: Baggins!
{DIALOGUE}: That will lead them here!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SHIRE LANE, SOUTH FARTHING -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: On a dark country lane, a Hobbit bounder lifts his watch lantern in alarm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HOBBIT BOUNDER
{DIALOGUE}: Halt!
{DIALOGUE}: Who goes there?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out of the darkness thunder two BLACK RIDERS...A LETHAL SWORD swings down at the small Hobbit bounder.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO thrusts the ring at Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Take it!
{DIALOGUE}: Take it!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 30.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, Frodo...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You must take it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You cannot offer me this ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I'm giving it to you!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Don't tempt me, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: I dare not take it, not even to keep it safe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: THE RING IN FRODO'S HAND...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Understand, Frodo...I would use this Ring from a desire to do good...but through me, it would wield a power too great and terrible to imagine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: But it cannot stay in the Shire!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, no it can't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: THE RING IN FRODO'S CLENCHED HAND.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What must I do?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRODO'S BEDROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: throwing clothes into a knapsack...Gandalf watches him, making plans...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You must leave, and leave quickly.
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of the Shire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Where?
{DIALOGUE}: Where shall I go?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Make for the village of Bree.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 31.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Bree?
{DIALOGUE}: What about you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I will, be waiting for you at the Inn of the Prancing Pony.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo packs his food into his knapsack.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: And the ring will be safe there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't have any answers.
{DIALOGUE}: I must see the Head of my Order.
{DIALOGUE}: He is both wise and powerful.
{DIALOGUE}: Trust me, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: He'll know what to go.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAG END LIVING ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is preparing to leave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to leave the name of Baggins behind you...for that name is not safe outside the Shire.
{DIALOGUE}: GANDALF helps FRODO into his coat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Travel only by day and stay off the road.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (thinking)
{DIALOGUE}: I can cut across country easily enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at the young Hobbit, moved by his courage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: My dear Frodo, Hobbits really are amazing creatures.
{DIALOGUE}: You can learn all that there is to know about their ways in a month, and yet, after a hundred years, they can still surprise you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SOUND from outside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Get down!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF FREEZES... he moves quietly towards the window, eyes wide with tension.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his staff above the window, and slams it down on the intruder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THERE IS A YELP OF PAIN!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 32.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf hauls a small figure into the room...SAM GAMGEE sprawls across the floor!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up in terror as Gandalf looms over him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (angry)
{DIALOGUE}: Confound it all!
{DIALOGUE}: Samwise Gamgee, have you been eavesdropping?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I ain't been dropping no eaves, sir!
{DIALOGUE}: Honest.
{DIALOGUE}: I was just cutting the grass under the window there, if you follow me...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: It's a little late for trimming the hedges, don't you think?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I heard raised voices...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: What did you hear?
{DIALOGUE}: Speak!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (panicked)
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing important...that is, I heard a good deal about a ring...and a Dark Lord.
{DIALOGUE}: And something about the end of the world, but...Please, Mr. Gandalf, sir, don't hurt me!
{DIALOGUE}: Don't turn me into anything unnatural!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO SMILES
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Perhaps not.
{DIALOGUE}: I've thought of a better use for you.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBITON FIELDS -- PRE DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: HOBBITON...shrouded in a white veil of MIST.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER: To reveal Gandalf, Frodo and Sam hurrying across a ploughed field, away from Hobbiton!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf leads his Horse...Frodo and Sam are carrying knapsacks.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 33.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Come along, Samwise...keep up...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOBBITON WOODS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf leads Frodo and Sam under the cover of Woods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Be careful, both of you.
{DIALOGUE}: The Enemy has many spies in his service, many ways of hearing...birds, beasts...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf takes Frodo to one side...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (low voice)
{DIALOGUE}: Is it safe?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO NODS...he pats his pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Never put it on, for then the agents of the Dark Lord will be drawn to its power...Always remember, Frodo, the ring is trying to get back to its master...it wants to be found.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf wheels his horse and gallops away.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GREEN HILL COUNTRY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MONTAGE: FRODO AND SAM hiking over the gentle Shire Countryside...wading through a shallow stream...heating a kettle over a small fire...clambering over stone walls.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GREEN HILL COUNTRY -- AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam stops short...taking stock of his surroundings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks back from where they came.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: This is it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: This is what?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 34.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: If I take one more step it'll be the farthest away from home I've ever been.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO gives Sam a pat on the shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Sam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam takes a deep breath and steps forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: SAM'S brown, furry foot hits the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO IS SMILING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Remember what Bilbo used to say...it's a dangerous business...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo and Sam continue their journey.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ... it's a dangerous business, Frodo, going out your door...you step onto the road, and if you don't keep your feet, there's not knowing where you might be swept off to.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD VALLEY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is galloping along the outskirts of the ancient forest of Fangorn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nestled in a basin at the foot of the distant Misty Mountains, the tall black tower of Orthanc is clearly visible
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD VALLEY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf gallops through the gate, into the fortress of ISENGARD...a great ring-wall of stone, a mile from rim to rim, encloses beautiful trees and gardens, watered by streams that flow down from the mountains.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Smoke rises once more from the mountain of doom...the shadow takes shape in the darkness of Mordor; the hour grows late...and Gandalf the Grey rides to Isengard seeking my counsel...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The strange tower of Orthanc...hewn from a solid pillar of black obsidian...rises up in the center of the Isengard Circle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf arrives at the foot of the Orthanc Stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 35.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SARUMAN, THE WHITE WIZARD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: he sweeps down the Orthanc stairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: For that is why you have come, is it not, my old friend?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf moves quickly towards him, grimy and weary from his long ride.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Saruman!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD GARDENS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf and Saruman walk slowly between the beautiful trees of Isengard, Saruman's clean, white robe contrasts with Gandalf's dusty grey robes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure of this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Beyond any doubt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: So the ring of power has been found?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: All these long years it was in the Shire, under my very nose.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: And yet you did not have the wit to see it!
{DIALOGUE}: Your love of the Halfling's leaf has clearly slowed your mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: We still have time...time enough to counter Sauron...if we act quickly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Time?
{DIALOGUE}: What time do you think we have?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ORTHANC ANTE-CHAMBER -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman and Gandalf are seated in a small, cluttered room to the side of the cavernous central chamber.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 36.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron has regained much of his former strength.
{DIALOGUE}: He cannot yet take physical form...but his spirit has lost none of its potency.
{DIALOGUE}: Concealed within his fortress, the lord of Mordor sees all.
{DIALOGUE}: His gaze pierces cloud, shadow, earth, and flesh.
{DIALOGUE}: You know of what I speak, Gandalf...a great Eye, lidless, wreathed in flame.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: The eye of Sauron.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: He is gathering all evil to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Very soon he will have summoned an army great enough to launch an assault upon Middle earth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: You know this?
{DIALOGUE}: How?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I have seen it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf and Saruman stride through Orthanc toward a stone plinth on which a sphere like shape is draped with a cloth...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: A palantir is a dangerous tool, Saruman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman lifts the cloth to reveal the Palantir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{DIALOGUE}: Why should we fear to use it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: They are not all accounted for, the lost seeing-stones...we do not know who else may be watching.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf throws the cloth back over the Palantir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLASH IMAGE: A FIERY EYE!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman sits upon his throne.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 37.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: The hour is later than you think.
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron's forces are already moving...the Nine have left Minas Morgul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (shocked)
{DIALOGUE}: The nine!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: They crossed the river Isen in Midsummer's eve, disguised as riders in black.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (alarmed)
{DIALOGUE}: They have reached the Shire?
{DIALOGUE}: Saruman shrugs...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: They will find the ring...and kill the one who carries it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf backs away and turns to run to the door...horrified as the doors suddenly slam shut.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You did not seriously think a Hobbit could contend with the will of Sauron?
{DIALOGUE}: There are none who can.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf slowly turns to Saruman...a look of dawning horror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Against the power of Mordor, there can be no victory.
{DIALOGUE}: We must join with him, Gandalf.
{DIALOGUE}: We must join with Sauron.
{DIALOGUE}: It would be wise, my friend.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (deadly)
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me, friend, when did Saruman the wise abandon reason for madness?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At that moment: Gandalf is suddenly blasted across the room!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slams against the wall...pinned there by some unseen force.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With sudden effort, Gandalf wrenches himself off the wall and swings his staff on Saruman...blasting him off his feet!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf and Saruman battle, powerful blasts throwing them across the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SARUMAN SCREAMS, EYES BLAZING!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf's staff is suddenly wrenched from his grasp...it flies across the chamber into Saruman's hand!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is flung to the floor.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 38.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I gave you the chance of aiding me willingly, but you have elected the way of pain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is breathing hard on the floor, his eyes look into the madness of Saruman... Commanding two staffs, Saruman sends Gandalf into a sickening spin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf tumbles towards the top of the chamber...as if falling in reverse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rushing POV: the roof of Orthanc rockets toward camera.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FARMER'S FIELDS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: Frodo and Sam walking along a country lane which borders Farmer Maggot's Fields.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam is looking up...Frodo has disappeared around a corner in the lane.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (panicked)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo turns, surprised as Sam comes running towards him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (worried)
{DIALOGUE}: I thought I lost you.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo looks at Sam suspiciously.
{DIALOGUE}: Sam glances down, embarrassed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (teasing)
{DIALOGUE}: What are you talking about?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (mumbling)
{DIALOGUE}: It's just something Gandalf said...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What did he say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: He said..."Don't you leave him, Samwise Gamgee."
{META_DATA}: (looks at Frodo intently)
{DIALOGUE}: And I don't mean to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (laughing)
{DIALOGUE}: Sam...we're still in the Shire...what could possibly happen?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 39.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A figure comes crashing out of a hedgerow sending Frodo flying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo picks himself up, only to be knocked back down again by Pippin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Merry, it's Frodo Baggins.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Hello Frodo
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry, Pippin, and Frodo picking themselves up... a variety of vegetables have scattered everywhere.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: What's the meaning of this!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Sam, hold this...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry gives Sam a large cabbage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (accusing)
{DIALOGUE}: You've been into Farmer Maggot's crop!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A large pitchfork can be seen racing towards them along the Hedgerow...angry shouts from Farmer Maggot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FARMER MAGGOT (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Who's that in my field!
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of it!
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of my field, you young varmits!
{DIALOGUE}: I'll show you...get out of my corn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry and Pippin hurriedly gather their booty and race away...with Frodo and Sam on their heels.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (looking behind him)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know why he's so upset, it's only a couple of carrots.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: And some cabbages...and those three bags of potatoes that we lifted last week.
{DIALOGUE}: And then the mushrooms the week before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, Pippin, my point is, he's clearly over reacting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BAYING OF LARGE DOGS sounds!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 40.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WOODED ROAD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, and Merry and Pippin tumble head over heels down a bank, onto a dark, wooded road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: A winded Pippin, his face inches away from a large pile of Horse droppings...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: That was close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo picks himself up and looks around quickly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (groaning)
{DIALOGUE}: Ow...I think I've broken something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulls a LARGE CARROT, almost broken through in the middle, out from his back pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (turning on Merry and Pippin)
{DIALOGUE}: Trust a Brandybuck and a Took.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{DIALOGUE}: That was just a detour...a shortcut.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: A shortcut to what?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin has spied something under the trees on the far side of the road.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{META_DATA}: (excited)
{DIALOGUE}: Mushrooms!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: SMALL, brown mushrooms growing amongst the Loamy undergrowth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam, Merry, and Pippin race toward the mushrooms!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is tense and watchful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He realizes they are on a wooded road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scattered leaves rise into the air Whirling down the road as if blown by an invisible wind...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 41.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY... THE SOUND OF HORSES HOOVES...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I think we should get off the road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long drawn WAIL comes down the wind, like the cry of some evil and lonely creature.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (more urgency)
{DIALOGUE}: Get off the road!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam grabs Merry and Pippin as the Hobbits quickly scramble down the bank, hiding under a mossy log.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE SOUND OF HOOVES is close... A sinister MOUNTED RINGWRATH steps into view...hooded and faceless, mounted on a huge snarling black horse with insane eyes !
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo freezes in terror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The RINGWRAITH pauses right beside their hiding place...he sits very still with his head bowed, listening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From inside the hood comes a sniffing noise as if he is trying to catch an elusive scent; his head turning from side to side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beads of sweat gather on his brow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ringwraith suddenly slides off his horse, leaning over the mossy log, peering suspiciously into the woods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is drawing the ring out of his pocket, with trembling hands...his face fevered and sweating as if in the grip of some terrible INTERNAL STRUGGLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SOUND OF SNIFFING intensifies as the ringwraith darts his head from side to side like a bird of party.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO SQUEEZING HIS EYES SHUT...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK PSYCHIC BLASTS!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AND EVIL DARK TOWER...A GREAT EYE...A
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BURST OF FLAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SAM LOOKING AT FRODO WITH CONCERN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry desperately hurls the mushrooms across the road...the ringwraith spins around at the sound, and darts to the far side of the road with frightening speed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo instantly slumps...as if a PSYCHIC LINK had been broken
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 42.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: What was that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is staring, a look of shock on his face at the ring lying in the palm of his hand.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FERRY LANE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin hurry through the trees...slipping and sliding on the muddy ground.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: What is going on?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry moves past pippin, toward Frodo, watching intently...Sam keeps looking around nervously.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: The Black rider was looking for something...or someone...Frodo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Get down!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SILHOUETTE OF A BLACK RIDER looms against the skyline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Four Hobbits... sprawled on the ground, holding their breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BLACK RIDER turns and departs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I have to leave the Shire...Sam and I must get to Bree.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry looks at his friend...realizing Frodo is in deep trouble.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Right...Buckleberry Ferry...follow me !
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hobbits break cover.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY, A RINGWRAITH bursts out of the forest TOWARD THEM!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: There's another one!!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo, this way!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hobbits run THE RINGWRAITH SHRIEKS!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK CUTS:
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 43.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black horse hooves... snarling horse mouths...a fleeting black cowl.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo, follow me!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUCKLEBERRY FERRY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO, SAM, MERRY AND PIPPIN, are running towards the wide, placid Brandywine river...and the FERRY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Get the ropes, Sam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK ANGLES: STOMPING HOOVES...SNARLING HORSES...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Four RINGWRAITHS are speeding through the Fog...converging on the FERRY CROSSING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HOBBITS stampede across the Wharf and Tumble onto the Ferry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (screaming)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo races across the Wooden Wharf, followed by the ringwraiths.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaps into the Ferry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: HOOVES THUNDER DOWN THE WOODEN WHARF!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam and Merry shove off with the poles...the ferry slides out into the river, just as the ringwraiths arrive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pull up on the end of the wharf... shrieking with rage!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hobbits cover their ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ringwraiths wheel their horses towards the north and Gallop away along the river bank, quickly disappearing into the fog.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: How far to the nearest crossing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: The brandwine bridge...twenty miles.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BREE GATE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lights of Bree...a small village of stone and half timbered houses nestled against a low wooded hill.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 44.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A thick hedge surrounds the village...a great gate bars the western entrance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO, SAM, MERRY AND PIPPIN approaching the gatehouse...wild eyes, ragged, and out of breath.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SURLY GATEKEEPER glances down at them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GATEKEEPER
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: We're headed for the prancing pony.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gatekeeper swings his lantern onto the hobbits, bathing them in an uncomfortable yellow spotlight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GATEKEEPER
{DIALOGUE}: Hobbits!
{DIALOGUE}: Four Hobbits, and what's more, out of the Shire by your talk.
{DIALOGUE}: What business brings you to Bree?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: We wish to stay at the inn...our business is our own.
{DIALOGUE}: To Frodo's relief, the Gatekeeper unlocks the gate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GATEKEEPER
{DIALOGUE}: All right, young sir, I meant no offense.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hobbits gratefully enter Bree...the gatekeeper eyeing them curiously in the lantern light.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GATEKEEPER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It's my job to ask questions after nightfall.
{DIALOGUE}: There's talk of strange fold abroad...can't be too careful.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BREE STREETS -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tall BREE FOLK loom over the nervous little hobbits as Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin make their way through the Narrow Streets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tall buildings tower above them...lights glow dimly from behind thick curtains.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 45.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: The sign of the "PRANCING PONY INN"...Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin hurry toward it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. "PRANCING PONY" RECEPTION -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin come rushing in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo attracts the INN KEEPERS'S attention.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTTERBUR
{DIALOGUE}: Good evening, little masters.
{DIALOGUE}: If you're seeking accommodation, we've got some nice, cozy Hobbit sized rooms available, Mr..
{DIALOGUE}: ah...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Underhill...my name's Underbill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTTERBUR
{DIALOGUE}: Underhill?
{DIALOGUE}: Hmmmm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: We're friends of Gandalf the Grey...can you tell him we've arrived?
{DIALOGUE}: BUTTERBUR frowns...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTTERBUR
{META_DATA}: (Puzzled)
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf...Gandalf...Oh...
{META_DATA}: (recognition)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh yes!
{DIALOGUE}: I remember...elderly chap...big grey beard...pointy hat?
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo nods with relief...Butterbur shakes his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTTERBUR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Not seen him for six months.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo is shocked.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (worried whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: What do we do now?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRANCING PONY INN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: the noise, smokey Inn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is dimly lit, cheifly from a blazing log fire...and crowded with a mixture of BIG FOLK, LOCAL HOBBITS, and a couple of dwarfs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin are sitting at a table against the wall... clearly trying to remain Quiet and inconspicuous... Sam can't help himself...he keeps casting nervous glances around.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 46.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Sam, he'll be here.
{DIALOGUE}: He'll come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry ploinks himself down at a table, carrying a very large mug of beer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: What's that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: This, my friend, is a pint.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: It comes in pints?
{DIALOGUE}: I'm getting one!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam watches Pippin rise unsteadily to his feet and head to the bar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: You've had a whole half already.
{DIALOGUE}: Merry watches Pippin go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A COUPLE OF SWARTHY MEN leaning against the bar glance at Frodo, then quickly look away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (tense)
{DIALOGUE}: That fellow's done nothing but stare at you since we've arrived.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam indicates a BROODING STRANGER who sits alone at a table in the far corner, smoking a curiously carved long stemmed pipe, peering from beneath a travel stained cowl with gleaming eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo gestures to Butterbur...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me, that man in the corner, who is he?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUTTERBUR
{DIALOGUE}: He's one of them Rangers; they're dangerous folk they are, wandering the wilds.
{DIALOGUE}: What his right name is, I never heard, but round here he's known as Strider.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: Strider.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BENEATH TABLE: FRODO'S fingers are nervously TOYING WITH THE RING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 47.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sweat runs down his brow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Strange hum of the Ring spills into the Soundtrack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Baggins...Baggins..." a creepy whisper seems to fill Frodo's head...sound that dissolves into Pippin's loud voice:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Baggins?
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, I know a Baggins...he's over there...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: PIPPIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sitting at the bar, chatting with Locals.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo leaps to his feet and pushes his way towards the bar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{META_DATA}: (loudly)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo Baggins.
{DIALOGUE}: He's my second cousin once removed, on his mother's side and my third cousin twice removed on his father's side...if you follow me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo grabs Pippin's sleeve, spilling his beer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Pippin!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Steady on, Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin pushes Frodo away...he stumbles backwards, and falls to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At that instant, the Inn goes silent and all the attention turns to Frodo...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ring...in agonizing Slow motion we watch as it seems to hang in the air for a split second...then crashes down onto his out stretched finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO VANISHES!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a sharp intake of breath...followed by total silence.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BREE COUNTRYSIDE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The RINGWRAITHS turn sharply in their saddles...Instantly aware that the ring is being worn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They spur their horses towards the distant lights of Bree.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 48.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. "PRANCING PONY" INN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks sick; Pippin instantly sobers, realizing his folly; the brooding stranger frowns...and the inn erupts into excited babble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE TWILIGHT WORLD:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO: as he finds himself in the TWILIGHT WORLD of the ring: THE EXCITED CROWD ARE suddenly moving in slow motion...distorted voices...a weird photographic negative quality.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO is moving in real time; against the slow motion background.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He suddenly clutches his head as he is hit with quick images...of a GREAT EYE!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN EVIL CAT-LIKE EYE, wreathed in flames.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VOICE OF SAURON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is no life here in the void...only cold...only death... FRODO is terrified!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls under a table, desperately pulling the ring from his finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO MATERIALIZES into the real world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THAT MOMENT: A LARGE HAND reaches under the table and Grabs Frodo by the collar, and DRAGS HIM AWAY!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRANCING PONY--CORRIDOR -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is roughly pushed against the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Brooding stranger looms over him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: You draw far too much attention to yourself...Mr. Underhill
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOBBIT'S ROOM, PRANCING PONY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is pushed into the Hobbit's room by Strider.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: A little more caution from you...that is no trinket you carry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I carry nothing.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 49.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Indeed?
{DIALOGUE}: I can usually avoid being seen if I wish, but to disappear entirely... that is a rare gift.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Are you frightened?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Not nearly frightened enough.
{DIALOGUE}: I know what hunts you.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo jumps at the sound of a noise in the corridor.
{DIALOGUE}: Strider deftly draws his sword.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door bursts open and Sam, Merry and Pippin appear on the doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam is Squaring off with is fists, Merry brandishes a candlestick, and Pippin a chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (angry)
{DIALOGUE}: Let him go or I'll have you, Longshanks!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STRIDER SHEATHS his sword, a slight smile playing on his lips.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: You have a stout heart, little Hobbit, but that alone won't save you...You can no longer wait for the Wizard, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: They're coming.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GATEHOUSE, BREE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gate keeper comes out of his Lodgings with a lantern...a look of fear on his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He approaches the closed gate with great apprehension.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: The Gatekeeper peers out of his Peephole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRASH!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gate crashed down on the gatekeeper...as four RINGWRAITHS ride into Bree!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 50.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BREE STREETS -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The four RINGWRAITHS fly done the empty streets, like horsemen of the apocalypse.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRANCING PONY INN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE: the front door FLIES OPEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The FOUR RINGWRAITHS rush into the PRANCING PONY with WICKED SWORDS DRAWN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: BUTTERBUR hiding behind his bar... trembling and sweating in TERROR.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOBBIT'S ROOM, PRANCING PONY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT: MERRY SNORING SOFTLY ON HIS PILLOW.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT: PIPPIN stirs slightly, then settles back to sleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: the door creaks open...THE FOUR RINGWRAITHS silently slide into the Hobbit's room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The LOOM above each bed, raising their SHINING SWORDS ABOVE THE SLEEPING HOBBITS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK INSERT: Sam's eyes open wide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In unison, the RINGWRAITS STAB THE HOBBITS, in a Slashing, hacking frenzy.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STRIDER'S ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider is grimly listening to the sounds from his room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOBBIT'S ROOM, PRANCING PONY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: the RINGWRAITHS step back from the slashed beds in triumph.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: a hacked blanket is pulled back to reveal nothing but a shredded pillow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The RINGWRAITHS SHRIEK WITH RAGE!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERTS: Sam sits up with a start!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Another shredded pillow is revealed!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More Shrieks of rage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT: PIPPIN AND MERRY wake with a start.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STRIDER'S ROOM -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: Sam, Merry, and Pippin have been sleeping on Strider's bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo stands next to Strider by the window, peering out nervously as furious Ringwraith screeches echo across the courtyard from the Hobbits room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Where are they?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: They were once men.
{DIALOGUE}: Strider glances quickly at Frodo, then looks away...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 51.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Great Kings of men.
{DIALOGUE}: Then Sauron the deceiver gave to them Nine Rings of Power.
{DIALOGUE}: Blinded by their greed they took them without question, one by one falling into darkness and now they are slaves to his will.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider looks from the window as the Ringwraiths gallop down the Bree Streets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Strider turns back to the Hobbits, his face lit faintly by the Glowing Embers of the Fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: They are the Nazgul, Ringwraiths, neither living or dead.
{DIALOGUE}: At all times they feel the presence of the ring...drawn to the power of the one.
{DIALOGUE}: they will never stop hunting you.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CHETWOOD FOREST -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STRIDER, MERRY, PIPPIN, AND FRODO march through a gloomy, overgrown forest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam follows at the read leading "Bill", a scrawny pony, who is laden with supplies.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you taking us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Into the wild.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo watches uneasily as Strider moves off into the cover of the trees...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (whispered aside)
{DIALOGUE}: How do, we know this Strider is a friend of Gandalf?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: We have no choice but to trust him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: But where is he leading us?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 52.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider stops, casts a glance back at Sam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: To Rivendell, Master Gamgee...to the house of Elrond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAM looks excited.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Did you hear that, Bill?
{DIALOGUE}: Rivendell!
{DIALOGUE}: We're going to see the Elves!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider leads the Hobbits through the gloom of the forest.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MIDGEWATER MOORS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aerial on: Strider leading Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin across the windswept moors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hobbits suddenly stop and unstrap their knapsacks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Gentlemen, we do not stop until nightfall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: What about breakfast?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: You've already had it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: We've had one, yes...but what about Second Breakfast?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider stares at Pippin blankly, then turns away, shaking his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think he knows about second breakfast, Pip.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: What about Elvenses, Luncheon, Afternoon Tea, dinner...he knows about them, doesn't he?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: I wouldn't count on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An apple is thrown to Merry, who deftly catches it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another, aimed at Pippin, catches him on the forehead.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 53.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (exasperated)
{DIALOGUE}: Pippin!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hobbits trudge through rain, looking tired, hungry, and miserable.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ORTHANC ANTE-CHAMBER -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman stands over the Palantir, his hands cupping the massive eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{META_DATA}: (whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: The power of Isengard is at your command, Sauron, Lord of the Earth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE SOUNDTRACK: BLACK SPEECH FILLS THE ROOM...ADMIST THE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HARSH, GUTTURAL WORDS THE VOICE OF SARUMAN EMERGES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Build me an army worth of Mordor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ORTHANC ANTE-CHAMBER -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman is seated as his ORC OVERSEER approaches.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ORC OVERSEER
{DIALOGUE}: What orders from Mordor, my Lord.
{DIALOGUE}: What does the eye command?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: We have work to do.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ISENGARD -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: GANDALF...lying unconscious on a cold obsidian floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wakes to the sound of ripping and tearing...rising onto his knees...lifting his head... Gandalf stands as the camera pulls back to reveal him stranded on the summit of Orthanc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is marooned on the tiny, flat peak, surrounded on all sides by a sheer 500 FOOT DROP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another whispering wail rends the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf crosses quickly to the edge and peers down: POV: One of the beautiful Isengard trees is being ripped from the ground by the ORCS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks on in Horror as ORCS hack into the trunk with axes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 54.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SARUMAN stands in Rain looking out into the dark night...the ORC overseer sidles up to him, axe in hand, sweating with exertion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ORC OVERSEER
{DIALOGUE}: The trees are strong, my Lord.
{DIALOGUE}: Their roots go deep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Rip them all down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA CIRCLES SUMMIT: MORE AND MORE TREES are hauled down and killed...as Gandalf looks on in helpless despair.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEATHERHILLS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: The rugged countryside as the hobbits journey on, lead by Strider.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider stops before a distant hill, topped by an Ancient Ruin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: This was once the great Watchtower of Amon Sul.
{DIALOGUE}: We shall rest here tonight.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEATHERTOP HOLLOW -- DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO, MERRY, AND PIPPIN collapse into a small hollow, halfway up Weathertop...they are muddy and exhausted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stider drops 4 small swords at the Hobbits feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: There are for you.
{DIALOGUE}: Keep them close.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to have a look around.
{DIALOGUE}: Stay here.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEATHERTOP HOLLOW -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo...eyes flickering open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He suddenly sits up, sniffing the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam, Merry, and Pippin huddled over a small fire... Sausages and bacon sizzle in a hot frying pan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Tomatoes, sausages, and crispy bacon.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 55.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: We saved some for you, Mr. Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Put it out, you fools!
{DIALOGUE}: Put it out!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo desperately kicks dirt on the fire!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, that's nice...ash on my tomatoes!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SUDDEN SHREIK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIVE RINGWRAITHS ON FOOT, running up the steep slope unnaturally fast.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin clamber desperately towards the summit, clutching their swords.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEATHERTOP SUMMIT -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin race into a RING OF BROKEN STONES on the summit or Weathertop...the ruined base of an ancient tower.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hobbits stand back-to-back in the centre of the Ring, waiting for the first assault... One by one, the 5 Ringwraiths appear...brandishing Gleaming swords, they move slowly towards the hobbits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the center is their leader...the WITCH KING!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Back, you devils!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam rushes forward with a cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He swings his sword at the Witch King, who blocks the blow with his own sword.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam's blade shatters...the WITCH KING lashes out with his fist, sending Sam flying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry and Pippin, overcome with terror, throw themselves flat on the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE RINGWRAITHS close in on Frodo...a Venomous whisper dances in his head...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo shuts his eyes and staggers back, desperately resisting the WRAITH'S WHISPERINGS... slow motion as his hand goes into his pocket and pulls out the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 5 Ringwraiths utter a chilling SCREECH OF EXCITEMENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is unable to resist any longer, falls to his knees and slips on the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He disappears.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 56.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE TWILIGHT WORLD:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo finds himself in the weird twilight world...he looks upon the Ringwraiths, now visible in their TRUE APPEARANCE: Five Ghouls dressed in long Grey robes, with white hair, and Pallid, ruthless faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE WITCH KING extends a haggard hand towards Frodo, reaching for the ring on his finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo's trembling hand extends forward as if by the pull of the ring...he slides to the ground, unable to pull his hand away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The witch king snarls and springs forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stabs at Frodo with a wicked dagger!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo winces as the tip of the dagger sinks into his shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, Strider charges at the RINGWRAITHS, wielding his sword in one hand, a flaming torch in the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves in slow motion, visible through a sea of mist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo sinks to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him is a faint image of a Ringwraith fleeing, his head engulfed in flames.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With draining strength, Frodo manages to pull the ring off his finger...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE REAL WORLD:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...Appearing back in the real world, Sam rushes over to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (horrified)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another Ringwraith is burning and screaming...others screech fearfully at the flames, turn and flee form the Weathertop summit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (panicked)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider kneels before Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He snatches up the Witch King's Dagger from the ground, staring gravely at the long, thin, blade.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Help him, Strider!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{META_DATA}: (grim)
{DIALOGUE}: He's been stabbed by a Morgul blade.
{DIALOGUE}: The Morgul Blade suddenly melts...vanishing into the air like smoke.
{DIALOGUE}: Strider throws the hilt down in disgust...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 57.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Do something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: This is beyond my skill to heal.
{META_DATA}: (urgently)
{DIALOGUE}: He needs Elvish medicine.
{DIALOGUE}: Strider lifts Frodo onto his shoulders.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEATHERHILLS -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider is jogging grimly, carrying an ailing Frodo on his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam, Merry, and Pippin are running to keep up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hobbits are carrying Flaming torches for protection.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: We are six days from Rivendell.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo groans.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: Hold on, Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: He'll never make it!
{DIALOGUE}: Close on: Frodo...head lolling about, barely conscious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (fevered calling)
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf...Gandalf?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Low angle...looking up at ORTHANC...the tower of Isengard, gleaming in the moonlight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera rises to reveal the once beautiful gardens are not a pitted wasteland...with smoke and fire billowing out
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: of numerous tunnels and vent holes that litter the forecourt of ORTHANC.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strange guttural chants echo up from deep underground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera is rising...a small moth flutters into shot...and leads the camera towards the summit or Orthanc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf lies slumped against the wall at the very top of Orthanc, surrounded by a sheer 500 foot drop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks Weak and Frail...and is seemingly asleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The MOTH flutters close to Gandalf.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand suddenly moves at lighting speed and SNATCHES THE MOTH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf brings his hand close to his face and opens it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The moth sits on the palm of his hand as Gandalf mutter strange words in a foreign tongue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: THE MOTH'S face... seemingly listening.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 58.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It suddenly flutters away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA FOLLOWS the moth off the Orthanc summit, but drops past the moth...falling down, down, towards the pitted wasteland, straight into a fiery red tunnel!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAVERNS BELOW ISENGARD -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dead trees of Isengard are fed into roaring furnaces...molten metal pours into casts...red hot metal, beaten my sweating orc blacksmiths...armor and weapons are forged from the great furnaces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman strides among the ORCS and stands looking on a new born uruk-hai as it escapes its birthing membrane...this is LURTZ, who rises up to stand before his master.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. TROLLSHAW FOREST CLEARING -- NIGHT
