{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE EAST ROAD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The white horse speeds out of the pine trees...the 4 ringwraiths close behind PAN ONTO: 2 more ringwraiths galloping down the hillside!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AERIAL SHOT: 3 MORE RINGWRAITHS enter frame from different directions...a total of 9 RINGWRAITHS now pursuing Frodo and Arwen!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Panting head of the WHITE ELVEN HORSE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{DIALOGUE}: Noro lim, Asfaloth!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FORD OF BRUINEN -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANE DOWN: As the White Horse races towards Camera, to Reveal the wide river Bruinen in the foreground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without hesitation, the white horse leaps into the shallow water and thunders across the Ford.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 9 Ringwraiths pull up short of the Ford, clearly nervous of the water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The white horse reaches the other side...Arwen pulls up and turns to defiantly face the Ringwraiths from across the Ford.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WITCH KING
{DIALOGUE}: Give up the Halfling, she-elf!
{DIALOGUE}: She draws her sword and yells at the Witch King.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{META_DATA}: (yelling)
{DIALOGUE}: If you want him, come and claim him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE WITCH KING SCREECHES ANGRILY, draws his sword, and leads the Ringwraiths across the Ford.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The water starts flowing faster...a distant rumble can be heard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen waits until they are halfway across: she suddenly stands in the saddle arms raised!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (Elvish)
{DIALOGUE}: Non o Chithaeglir, lasto Beth daer: Rimmo nin Briunen Dan in Ulaer!
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 63.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Nin o Chitaeglir, lasto Beth daer: Rimmo nin Bruinen Dan in Ulaer!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE GROUND SUDDENLY TREMBLES...A MIGHTY ROAR FILLS THE AIR!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks up weakly...to see a vast torrent of Water flooding down the river towards the ford...as if a dam had burst!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Foaming water seems to form the shape of Dancing white horses with frothing manes!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ringwraiths scream in terror as they are swallowed up in the deluge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their Piercing cries are drowned in the roaring of the river as it carries them away!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO as he loses consciousness...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{META_DATA}: (upset)
{DIALOGUE}: No, no...Frodo, no!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo, don't give in...not now!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen gathers the small Hobbit in her arms, feeling his life slip away.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRODO'S DELIRIUM -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DELIRIOUS IMAGES AND SOUNDS....
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What grace is given me, let it pass to him.
{DIALOGUE}: Let him be spared.
{DIALOGUE}: Save him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: A BRIGHT LIGHT suddenly flares...Frodo squeezes his eyes shut, gasping.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (frightened)
{DIALOGUE}: Where am I?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FAMILIAR VOICE cuts through the swirl of sound.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: You are in the House of Elrond, and it is ten o'clock in the morning on October the twenty-fourth, if you want to know.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRODO'S BEDROOM -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo's eyes flicker Open He is lying in bed next to an Open Window...Dappled sunlight plays on richly carved timbers...the sound of a nearby waterfall drifts through the Vista of Fir Trees.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (weak relief)
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 64.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: GANDALF IS SITTING NEXT TO FRODO'S BED...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: softly puffing on his pipe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles at Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I'm here and you're lucky to be here, too.
{DIALOGUE}: A few more hours and you would have been beyond our aid.
{DIALOGUE}: You have some strength in you, my dear Hobbit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo sits up, looking at Gandalf questioningly...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: What happened, Gandalf?
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you meet us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Gandalf... troubled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes drift away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I was delayed.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ORTHANC SUMMIT -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SARUMAN stands over Gandalf, gloating...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Get up!
{DIALOGUE}: So much for the power of the Ring or embrace your own destruction!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With the power of his staff, Saruman raises Gandalf from the ground, then sends him crashing to the floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: There is only one Lord of the Ring.
{DIALOGUE}: Only one who can bend it to his will...and he does not share power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF lurches to his feet and Throws himself off the Tower!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman watches Gandalf fly away from Isengard...on the Back of a GIANT EAGLE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{META_DATA}: (chilling)
{DIALOGUE}: So you have chosen death!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 65.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SKIES OVER MOUNTAINS--DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gwaihir the Eagle soars majestically over the mountains, carrying Gandalf towards the dawn.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRODO'S BEDROOM--RIVENDELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo raises himself up and looks at Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf!
{DIALOGUE}: What is it?
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf returns his attention to Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing, Frodo...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam runs to Frodo's bedside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is overjoyed to find Frodo awake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Bless you, you're awake!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Sam has hardly left your side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: We were worried about you--weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: By the skills of Lord Elrond, you're beginning to mend.
{DIALOGUE}: ELROND, LORD OF THE HIGH ELVES, steps up to Frodo's
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: bedside...his face is neither old nor young, though in it is written the memory of many things both glad and sorrowful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo sits up, looking at Elrond with awe.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL VALLEY -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: RIVENDELL... a small cluster of elegant Elven Buildings sitting in a Shangri-la like Valley below towering cliffs and snow capped mountains.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 66.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: You have found your way to the last homely house east of the sea.
{DIALOGUE}: The elves of Imladris have dwelt within this valley for three thousand years through few of my kin now remain.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo looks out from his balcony.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL GARDENS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo and Sam walk together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, the voices of Merry and Pippin can be heard as they bound up to Frodo and throw their arms around him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks past Frodo smiling... a bent figure sits alone on a bench, in the Sun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo turning, following Sam's gaze...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL TERRACE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: BILBO BAGGINS!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He breaks in to a broad grin as Frodo rushes forward to embrace him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo has aged significantly since we last saw him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, Frodo, my lad!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER... Frodo is turning the neatly inscribed title page of a red leather bound journal:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (reading)
{DIALOGUE}: "There and back again: A Hobbit's tale" by Bilbo Baggins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo smiles Proudly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is sitting with Frodo on a terrace overlooking a Waterfall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks at Page after page of beautiful Handwriting, with intricate Maps and Drawings.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 67.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: This is wonderful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: I meant to go back...wander the paths of Mirkwood, visit Laketown, see the Lonely Mountain again...but age, it seems, has finally caught up with me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo turns a page...there before him, is a map of the Shire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: I miss the Shire...I spent all my childhood pretending I was off somewhere else...off with you, on one of your adventures...
{META_DATA}: (Looks at Bilbo)
{DIALOGUE}: But my own adventure, turned out to be quite different...I'm not like you, Bilbo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: My dear boy...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL TERRACE -- EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam busily tries to stuff more and more things into his already full pack...pots and pans, blankets, cooking utensils, provisions, clothes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: No, what have I forgotten?
{DIALOGUE}: Pull back to reveal Frodo, hands in his pocket, watching Sam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Packed already?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks up, startled.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (slightly embarrassed)
{DIALOGUE}: No harm in being prepared.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo strolls to the edge of the Balcony.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you wanted to see the Elves, Sam?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 68.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I do...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: More than anything.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I did.
{DIALOGUE}: It's just...we did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?
{DIALOGUE}: We got the Ring this far, to Rivendell...and I thought... seeing as how you're on the mend, we'd be off soon.
{DIALOGUE}: Off home.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You're right, Sam.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo looks at Sam...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...we did what we set out to do.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo opens his hand, the Ring sits in his Palm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The ring will be safe in Rivendell.
{DIALOGUE}: I am ready to go home.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ELROND'S CHAMBER, RIVENDELL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf and Elrond watch Frodo and Sam from Elrond's balcony,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: His strength returns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: That wound will never fully heal.
{DIALOGUE}: He will carry it the rest of his life.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: And yet to have come so far still bearing the Ring...the hobbit has shown extraordinary resilience to its evil.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: It is a burden he should never have to had to bear.
{DIALOGUE}: We can ask no more of Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf, the enemy is moving.
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron's forces are massing in the east.
{DIALOGUE}: His eye is fixed on Rivendell.
{DIALOGUE}: And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.
{DIALOGUE}: Our list of allies grows thin.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 69.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: His treachery runs deeper than you know.
{DIALOGUE}: By foul craft, Saruman has crossed Orc with Goblin Men...he is breeding an army in the caverns of Isengard.
{DIALOGUE}: An army that can move in Sunlight and cover great distance at speed.
{DIALOGUE}: Saruman is coming for the Ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elrond turns and walks away...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: This evil cannot be concealed by the power of the Elves...We do not have the strength to fight both Mordor and Isengard...Gandalf...the ring cannot stay here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf turns and looks out the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sounds of arrivals...Gandalf watches as Boromir rides through Rivendell gate, followed by Legolas and Gimli.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: This peril belongs to all Middle earth.
{DIALOGUE}: They must decide how to end it.
{DIALOGUE}: Not just for themselves but for those who come after.
{DIALOGUE}: Elrond approaches Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The time of the Elves is over.
{DIALOGUE}: My people are leaving these shores.
{DIALOGUE}: Who will you look to when we have gone?
{DIALOGUE}: The dwarves?
{DIALOGUE}: They hide in their mountains seeking riches.
{DIALOGUE}: They care nothing for the troubles of others.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: It is in Men that we must place our hope.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Men?
{DIALOGUE}: Men are weak.
{DIALOGUE}: The race of Men is failing.
{DIALOGUE}: The blood of Numenor is all but spent, its pride and dignity forgotten.
{DIALOGUE}: It is because of men the Ring survives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLASH INSERT: With the broken sword, Isildur slices off Sauron's finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elrond reacts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I was there, Gandalf...I was there three thousand years ago when Isildur took the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 70.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLASH INSERT: ISILDUR PICKS UP THE RING AND STARES AT IT,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ENTRANCED.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: I was there the day the strength of Men failed.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CRACK OF DOOM -- DAY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Isildur...hurry...follow me!
{DIALOGUE}: IMAGES: ELROND leads Isildur into the steaming volcano.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I let Isildur into the heart of Mount Doom, where the ring was forged: the one place it could be destroyed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLASH INSERT: ELROND AND ISILDUR STAND BEFORE THE FIRES OF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MT. DOOM.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Cast it into the fire...destroy it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ISILDUR...CAPTIVATED BY THE RING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ISILDUR
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Isildur turns and walks away
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Isildur!!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ENROND'S CHAMBER, RIVERDELL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elrond turns to Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: It should have ended that day, but evil was allowed to endure.
{DIALOGUE}: Isildur kept the Ring...and the line of Kings was broken.
{DIALOGUE}: There's no strength left in the world of Men.
{DIALOGUE}: They're scattered, divided, leaderless.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 71.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: There is one who could unite them, one who could re claim the thrown of Gondor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: He turned from that path a long time ago.
{DIALOGUE}: He has chosen exile.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELROND'S CHAMBER, RIVENDELL -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider watches from the shadows...as Boromir strolls through the darkened gallery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir's eyes are drawn to an old Fresco on the wall...depicting Isildur defeating Sauron.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir looks with Wonderment at Narsil, the Broken Blade of Elendil, which lies on a cloth-covered plinth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (quiet awe)
{DIALOGUE}: The shards of Narsil...the blade that cut the Ring from Sauron's hand.
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir picks up the sword and gently touches the Blade.
{DIALOGUE}: Close on: a small bloom of blood appears on Boromir's finger...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Still sharp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir senses Strider's presence...he looks from the blade to Strider, as if sensing a connection.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: But no more than a broken heirloom.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: replaces the Broken blade, but it clatters to the floor.
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir walks away, leaving Strider sitting alone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Strider picks up the broken hilt, as Arwen appears behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you fear the past?
{DIALOGUE}: You are Isildur's heir...not Isildur himself.
{DIALOGUE}: You are not bound to his fate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: The same blood flows in my veins...the same weakness...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 72.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{DIALOGUE}: Your time will come.
{DIALOGUE}: You will face the same evil...and you will defeat it.
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: w/subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: A si i-duath u-orthor, Aragorn...u or le a u or nin.
{DIALOGUE}: The shadow does not hold sway yet...not over you and not over me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL VALLEY -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Night falls upon the beautiful valley of Rivendell... still and quiet.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL WATERFALL -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider and Arwen stand upon a stone bridge...the Evenstar at Arwen's breast shines in the moonlight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: with subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Renech I lu I erui govannem?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember when we first met?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: with subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Nauthannim I ned ol reniannen.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought I had strayed into a dream.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen reaches up and gently touches the Grey at Strider's temples.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: with subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Gwenin in enniath...u-arnech in naeth I se celich.
{DIALOGUE}: Long years have passed...you did not have the care you carry now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen looks into Strider's eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: with subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Renech I Beth I pennen?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember what I told you?
{DIALOGUE}: Arwen reaches for Strider's hand...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: You said you'd bind yourself to me, forsaking the immortal life of your people.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 73.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{META_DATA}: (whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: And to that I hold.
{DIALOGUE}: I would rather share one lifetime with you than face all the ages of this world alone.
{DIALOGUE}: Strider looks down.
{DIALOGUE}: In his hand lies the Evenstar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I choose a mortal live.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: You cannot give me this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARWEN
{DIALOGUE}: It is mine to give to whom I will, like my heart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen closes Strider's fingers around the jewel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arwen leans towards Strider, gently kissing him.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COUNCIL CHAMBER, RIVENDELL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elrond addresses the council...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: Strangers from distant lands ... friends of old.
{DIALOGUE}: You have been summoned here to answer the threat of Mordor.
{DIALOGUE}: Middle-earth stands upon the brink of destruction.
{DIALOGUE}: None can escape it.
{DIALOGUE}: You will unite...or you will fall.
{DIALOGUE}: Each race is bound to this fate...this one doom...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo sits amongst a council of free-peoples of Middle earth, Elrond stands before them, addressing Gandalf, Strider, Legolas, and 20 other elves, Dwarves, and men.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Bring forth the ring, Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo steps forward and moves towards a stone Plinth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He places the ring on the plinth and returns to his seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (shocked)
{DIALOGUE}: So it is true!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{META_DATA}: (disbelief)
{DIALOGUE}: Sauron's Ring!
{DIALOGUE}: The ring of power!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 74.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (grim)
{DIALOGUE}: The doom of man!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: It is a gift...a gift to the foes of Mordor!
{DIALOGUE}: Why not use this Ring?
{DIALOGUE}: Long has my father, the Steward of Gondor, held the forces of Mordor at bay...by the blood of our people are your lands kept safe.
{DIALOGUE}: Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy...let us use it against him!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STRIDER
{DIALOGUE}: You cannot wield it.
{DIALOGUE}: None of us can.
{DIALOGUE}: The one ring answers to Sauron alone...it has no other master.
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir turns and looks at Strider, coolly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: And what would a ranger know of this matter?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Strider says nothing and Boromir turns away dismissively.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LEGOLAS stands...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: This is no mere Ranger.
{DIALOGUE}: He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.
{DIALOGUE}: You owe him your allegiance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks at Strider questioningly...Boromir turns sharply.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (quiet disbelief)
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn?
{DIALOGUE}: This is Isildur's heir?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: And heir to the throne of Gondor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (Elvish: with subtitles)
{DIALOGUE}: Havo dad, Legolas...Sit down, Legolas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Gondor needs no king.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn is right...we cannot use it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: You have only one choice.
{DIALOGUE}: the ring must be destroyed.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 75.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HUM OF THE RING seems to grow louder in Frodo's ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli suddenly stands, excited.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: Then...what are we waiting for?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli suddenly rushes forward!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He swings his axe down on the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The axe shatters with a deafening crack!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli falls backwards, staring in disbelief at the ring...unharmed!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo winces as an angry image of the fiery eye hits him!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slumps in this chair, clutching his forehead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at him with concern.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: The ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli, son of Gloin, by any craft that we
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: here possess.
{DIALOGUE}: The ring was made in the fires of Mount Doom...only there can it be unmade.
{DIALOGUE}: It must be taken deep into Mordor, and cast back into the fiery chasm from whence it came.
{DIALOGUE}: One of you must do this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stunned silence...the council sits with downcast eyes, as if a great dread has descended on them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir addresses the council in a quiet voice
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: One does not simply walk into Mordor.
{DIALOGUE}: Its black gates are guarded by more than just Orcs.
{DIALOGUE}: There is evil there that does not sleep and the Great Eye is ever watchful.
{DIALOGUE}: It is a barren wasteland, riddled with fire and ash and dust...the very air you breathe is a poisonous fume.
{DIALOGUE}: Not with ten thousand men could you do this.
{DIALOGUE}: It is folly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond has said?
{DIALOGUE}: The ring must be destroyed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: And I suppose you think you're the one to do it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: And if we fail, what then?
{DIALOGUE}: What happens when Sauron takes back what is his?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli leaps to his feet!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 76.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (3)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: I will be dead before I see the Ring in the hands of an Elf!
{DIALOGUE}: A STORM OF ARGUMENT erupts around the room.
{DIALOGUE}: CLOSE ON: FRODO...sound disappears as he watches in slow
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: motion...the angry faces, the shaking fists, the accusatory fingers, his eyes move across to the ring...the hum grows louder in his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (shouting)
{DIALOGUE}: Never trust an Elf!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: THE RING fills the screen...streams of blood flow across the surface... flames flicker within the Gold Band.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Do you not understand?
{DIALOGUE}: While we bicker among ourselves, Sauron's power grows!
{DIALOGUE}: No one will escape it.
{DIALOGUE}: You will all be destroyed, your homes burnt and your families put to the sword!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO...breathing rapidly, Caught in the grip of his hideous vision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a huge effort or will, Frodo tears his gaze upon the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo suddenly stands...he speaks in a strong, clear voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I will take it...I will take it...I will take the Ring to Mordor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sudden silence...Frodo looks around the room at the astounded faces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Though...I do not know the way.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf rises to his feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I will help you bear this burden, Frodo Baggins, as long as it is yours to bear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: If, by my life or death, I can protect you, I will.
{META_DATA}: (kneels before Frodo)
{DIALOGUE}: ...you have my sword.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn steps forward...followed by Legolas and Gimli.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 77.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (4)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: And you have my bow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: And my axe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir looks at them all then walks towards Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: You carry the fate of us all, little one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir looks towards Elrond and Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: If this is indeed the will of the Council, then Gondor will see it done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo stares in wonder as the Greatest Fighters in all Middle earth stand at his side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (unseen)
{DIALOGUE}: Here!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Sudden Noise...Sam pops up from behind a Bush!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo's not gong anywhere without me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{DIALOGUE}: No, Indeed...it is hardly possible to separate you...even when he is summoned to a secret council and you are not.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry and Pippin jump up from behind another bush!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Oi!
{DIALOGUE}: We're coming too!
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to send us home tied up in a sack to stop us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway...you need people of intelligence on this sort of mission...quest...thing...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that rules you out, Pip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 78.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ELROND SURVEYS THE GROUP
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELROND
{META_DATA}: (thoughtfully)
{DIALOGUE}: Nine companions ... so be it.
{META_DATA}: (announcing)
{DIALOGUE}: You shall be the "Fellowship of the ring"
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Great.
{DIALOGUE}: Where are we going?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRODO'S BEDROOM, RIVERDELL---DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: An old sword sliding out of a shabby leather Scabbard...its polished, well tendered Blade glitters cold and bright.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: My old sword "Sting"...here, take it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo offers Sting to Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: It's so light!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, yes, made by the Elves, you know.
{DIALOGUE}: The blade glows blue when Orcs are close...and it's times like that, my lad, when you have to be extra careful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo unwraps a small shirt of close woven Mail.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Here's a pretty thing.
{DIALOGUE}: Mithril, as light as a feather, and as hard as dragon scales.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me see you put it on.
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Frodo peels off his shirt... revealing The Ring on the Chain around his neck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (entranced)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh!
{DIALOGUE}: My old Ring... Frodo frowns as Bilbo moves toward him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I should very much like to hold it again, one last time.
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo reaches forward, eyes locked on the ring.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 79.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shadow passes across Bilbo...for a split second he becomes a wrinkled creature with a hungry face and Bony, groping hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo pulls away, shocked...the shadow passes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo slumps into a chair, his head in his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo falters...his eyes filling with tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILBO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (sad)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, that I brought this upon you, my boy...I'm sorry that you must carry this burden.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry for everything.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bilbo sobs and Frodo moves to comfort him.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVENDELL VALLEY -- MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship climb the long steep path out of the cloven vale of Rivendell.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROUGH COUNTRY, SOUTH OF RIVENDELL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fellowship trekking through a land of Deep Valleys and turbulent waters...the misty mountains rise sharply to their left.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: We must hold to his course west of the misty Mountains for forty days.
{DIALOGUE}: If our luck holds, the Gap of Rohan will still be open to us.
{DIALOGUE}: From there, our road turns east, to Mordor.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. EREGION HILLS--DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Sam at the campfire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of clashing swords!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wider: Aragorn and Boromir are giving Pippin Sword tuition...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 80.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Get away from the blade, Pippin...on your toes...good, very good...I want you to react, not think.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Should not be too hard...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Move your feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Quite good, Pippin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: GIMLI has managed to corner Gandalf....
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: If anyone were to ask for my opinion, which I note they have not, I would say we are taking the long way round.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf, we can pass through the Mines of Moria.
{DIALOGUE}: My cousin, Balin, would give us a royal welcome.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf clearly thinks that is a bad idea.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, Gimli.
{DIALOGUE}: I would not take the road through Moria unless I had no other choice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir thrusts, catching Pippin on the hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin throws down his sword, kicks and lunges at Boromir, tackling him to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Much laughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas' eyes are fixed on a distant Dark Patch which darts about the sky, like flying smoke in the wind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: What is that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing...it's just a wisp of a cloud.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (worried)
{DIALOGUE}: It's moving fast...against the wind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: Crebain from Dunland!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 81.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (urgently)
{DIALOGUE}: Hide!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Merry.
{DIALOGUE}: Pippin...Sam...take cover!
{DIALOGUE}: WIDE ON: THE FELLOWSHIP scramble under what little cover
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: there is...as a regiment of Large crows fly low overhead at Great speed, wheeling and circling above.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As their dark shadow passes over the fellowship, a single harsh croak is heard...and the crows suddenly wheel away, back towards the south.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf staggers to his feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (worried)
{DIALOGUE}: Spies of Saruman.
{DIALOGUE}: The passage South is being watched.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at Aragorn, turns to the others...gesturing towards a high mountain pass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: We must take the pass of Caradhras!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SNOWY MOUNTAINSIDE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship clamber through Rock and Snow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Frodo slips on some shale...as he scrambles to his feet, the Ring falls on the ground... CLOSE ON: the ring gleaming in the snow!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir's Hand picks it up by the chain...he stands, the ring dangling before his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seems to grow in stature, as if absorbing its power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn warily approaches Boromir...Boromir is motionless...he stares at the ring, as if transfixed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: It is a strange fate that we should suffer so much fear and doubt over so small a thing...such a little thing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir...give the ring to Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: ARAGORN'S HAND moves to his sword hilt.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 82.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ring's POV...looking up at Boromir's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The strange hum vibrates on the soundtrack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: a Weird beatific smile lights up Boromir's face...The HUM grows to a Deafening roar!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir suddenly snaps out of his trance and hands the ring back to Frodo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (lightly)
{DIALOGUE}: As you wish.
{DIALOGUE}: I care not.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir smiles at Frodo, ruffling his hair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ARAGON unhands his sword.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Following the crows as they race deeper and deeper, passing a vista of Industry, Hundreds of Orcs and writhing Birthsacks...flying past Saruman, who stands upon a wooden Gantry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Saruman, listening to the Cries of the crows.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: So, Gandalf...you try to lead them over Caradhras.
{DIALOGUE}: And if that fails...where then will you go?
{DIALOGUE}: THE FELLOWSHIP struggles through the snow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: If the mountain defeats you, will you risk a more dangerous road?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PASS OF CARADHRAS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE FELLOWSHIP are struggling through a blinding blizzard, up towards the PASS OF CARADHRAS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas the Elf moves lightly across the top of the snow...he suddenly pauses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman's voice sweeps by in the wind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{META_DATA}: (urgent)
{DIALOGUE}: There is a fell voice in the air.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: It's Saruman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THUNDER RUMBLES...ROCK and Shale fall from above.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 83.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (urgently)
{DIALOGUE}: He's trying to bring down the mountain.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf!
{DIALOGUE}: We must turn back!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF RAISES HIS STAFF...HE CHANTS INTO THE WIND.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (YELLING)
{DIALOGUE}: Losto Caradhras, sedho, hodo, nuitho I ruith.
{DIALOGUE}: Sleep Caradhras, be still, lie still, hold your wrath.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA SWEEPS PAST SARUMAN...he stands on the summit of Orthanc, Chanting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOUDS ARE FLOWING FROM ALL DIRECTIONS... converging on the distant mountains in a stormy Malestrom.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PASS OF CARADHRAS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saruman's voice strengthens...rolling past the fellowship like thunder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LIGHTNING CRACK explodes on the mountainside above them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks up in horror as a huge snow avalanche thunders down towards them!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship throw themselves against the cliff face as snow crashes onto the narrow ledge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LEGOLAS pulls Gandalf to safety.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn shields Frodo and Sam as snow piles around them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Within moments, the pass is blocked and the fellowship are enveloped in snow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir and Aragorn frantically dig for the hobbits...who are pulled out Shivering and Fearful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (urgent)
{DIALOGUE}: We must get off the mountain!
{DIALOGUE}: Make for the gap of Rohan and take the West road to my city.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: The Gap of Rohan takes us too close to Isengard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: We cannot pass over the mountain.
{DIALOGUE}: Let us go under it.
{DIALOGUE}: Let us go through the mines of Moria.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf has a concerned look on his face.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 84.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Moria.
{DIALOGUE}: You fear to go into those mines, don't you?
{DIALOGUE}: The dwarves delved too greedily and too deep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You know what they awoke in, the darkness of Khazad-dum.
{DIALOGUE}: Shadow and flame.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Let the ringbearer decide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO, the weight of the decision weighing heavily upon him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: MERRY and PIPPIN shivering in Boromir's arms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo meets Gandalf's eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: We will go through the mines.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf slowly nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: So be it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MORIA GATE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship are walking along the far shore of dark lake...directly below great looming cliffs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (in awe)
{DIALOGUE}: The walls of Moria!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Footing is treacherous on the narrow strip of green and greasy stones.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf touches the smooth rock wall between the trees... slowly, faint lines appear like slender veins of luminous silver running through the stone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Itidin...it mirrors only starlight and moonlight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A large moon rises over the mountains... The lines grow Broader and Clearer, forming a glowing arch of interlacing ancient letters and symbols.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 85.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It reads, "The door of Durin, Lord of Moria.
{DIALOGUE}: Speak, friend, and enter."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: What do you suppose that means?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (confident)
{DIALOGUE}: It's quite simple.
{DIALOGUE}: If you are a friend, speak the password and the doors will open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf raises his arms...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (incanting)
{DIALOGUE}: Annon edhellen, edro hi ammen!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cliff towers into the night, the wind blows cold, Frodo shivers... and the door stands fast!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF CONTINUES...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mumbling spells in his efforts to open the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam packs pots and pans at his feet...watching sadly as Aragorn un- saddles Bill the pony.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ARAGORN whispering to Bill the Pony.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (whispering)
{DIALOGUE}: Mines are no place for a Pony, even one so brave as Bill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Bye, Bill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Go on, Bill, go on.
{DIALOGUE}: don't worry, Sam...he knows his way home.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn slaps Bill on the rump...Bill goes trotting off.
{DIALOGUE}: CLOSE ON: Sam watching Bill disappear into the darkness.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye, Bill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SPLASH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry and Pippin are tossing stones into the lake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black Rippling rings slowly fan out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin is about to throw another stone, but Aragorn grabs his arm.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 86.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (ominous)
{DIALOGUE}: Do not disturb the water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn watches anxiously as the Ripples appear to grow....he exchanges a look with Boromir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn's hand creeps towards his sword.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf gives up in despair...he sits down beside Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo peers at the Elvish inscription...his face breaks into a smile of comprehension.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: It's a riddle...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf raises his eyebrows...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (explaining)
{DIALOGUE}: Speak, friend, and enter.
{DIALOGUE}: What's the Elvish for friend?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Oh...mellon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With that, the rock face silently divides in the middle and two great Doors swing outwards... revealing a blackness deeper than the night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the Fellowship enter the Blackness, something in the water stirs....
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MORIA GATE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship step warily into the darkness of Moria...a Dank cavern, with winding steps leading deeper into the mountain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: So, master elf, you will enjoy the fabled hospitality of the dwarves; roaring fires, malt beer, red meat off the bone.
{DIALOGUE}: This, my friend, is the home of my cousin, Balin...and they call this a Mine...
{META_DATA}: (snorting)
{DIALOGUE}: A mine!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Glow from Gandalf's Staff suddenly lights the chamber... The Fellowship recoil in Horror!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Many dwarf Skeletons are strewn about, clearly the dead of some old battle...the rusting armor and shields are peppered with arrows and axes.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 87.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (grimly)
{DIALOGUE}: This is no mine...it's a tomb!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (in horror)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh...no...no.
{DIALOGUE}: no... !
{DIALOGUE}: Legolas pulls a crude arrow out of a skeleton.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: Goblins!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship draw swords and back away, towards the Entrance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: We make for the Gap of Rohan.
{DIALOGUE}: We should never have come here.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MORIA GATE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is suddenly PULLED TO THE GROUND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long sinuous Tentacle is wrapped around Frodo's ankle and is dragging him towards the lake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO CRIES OUT as Aragorn and Boromir rush forward!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn severs the Tentacle holding Frodo, and pulls him to safety...Boromir hacks at the other Writhing Limbs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 20 more tentacles ripple out of the Lake!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dark water Boils as the hideous beast lashes out at the FELLOWSHIP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Again the creature grabs Frodo and pulls him to the lake, Frodo is flung in the air as the Fellowship battle the creature.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn hacks at a tentacle...Frodo is released, falling into Boromir's arms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Into the mines!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Legolas!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas shoots an Arrow into the creature's head, gaining a few vital seconds for Aragorn and Boromir as they race out of the water with Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The FELLOWSHIP hurriedly back away from the Creature... retreating into the Moria Chamber as many Coiling arms seize the large doors.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MORIA GATE -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a shattering echo, the creature rips the doors away, creating a rock slide that crashes down the Cliff Face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Within seconds, tons of rock seal the doorway... throwing the Fellowship into Pitch Blackness.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 88.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A faint light rises from Gandalf's staff, throwing a Creepy Glow across the old wizards face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (ominous)
{DIALOGUE}: We now have but one choice...we must face the long dark of Moria.
{DIALOGUE}: Be on your guard...there are older and fouler things than the Orcs in the deep places of the world.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NEW CHAMBER, MORIA -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: the Fellowship crossing a precarious bridge above deep mine workings.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Quietly, now.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a four day journey to the other side.
{DIALOGUE}: Let us hope that our presence will go unnoticed.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MORIA CEMETERY CAVERN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They continue up a steep stair, passing through a dwarf cemetery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The graves are despoiled...dwarf skeletons are strewn about and Goblin Graffiti is scrawled on monuments in dried Dwarf blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Atmosphere is very sinister.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MORIA TUNNEL FORK -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The path splits into three passages...each disappearing into dark tunnels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf pauses, frowning.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: I have no memory of this place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER... The Fellowship are nervously waiting...while Gandalf sits, staring intently at the 3 tunnel mouths in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He appears to be in some kind of trance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns at the sound of a faint noise down the tunnel behind them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Are we lost?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 89.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think we are.
{DIALOGUE}: Shhhh, Gandalf's thinking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Merry!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm hungry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo's POV: a sudden glimpse of a creature darting in the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is nervous...he approaches Gandalf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRO DO
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: There's something down there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: It's Gollum.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Gollum!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: He's been following us for three days.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TEASING SHOT: and emaciated, leering creature.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (disbelieving)
{DIALOGUE}: He escaped the dungeons of Barad- dur?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Escaped...or was set loose.
{DIALOGUE}: And now the Ring has drawn him here...he will never be rid of his need for it.
{DIALOGUE}: He hates and loves the ring, as he hates and loves himself.
{DIALOGUE}: Smeagol's life is a sad story.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf catches Frodo's look of surprise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes...Smeagol he was once called...Before the ring came to him, before it drove him mad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gollum's withered fingers are gripping the cave wall...he is large, Luminous eyes blinking with malice.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 90.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (grim)
{DIALOGUE}: It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him when he had the chance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Pity?
{DIALOGUE}: It was pity that stayed Bilbo's hand.
{DIALOGUE}: Many that live deserve death, and some that die deserve life.
{DIALOGUE}: Can you give it to them, Frodo?
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo frowns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Do not be too eager to deal out death in judgment...even the very wise cannot see all ends.
{DIALOGUE}: My heart tells me that Gollum has some part to play yet, for good or ill, before this is over.
{DIALOGUE}: The pity of Bilbo may rule the fate of many.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I wish the ring had never come to me...I wish none of this had happened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: So do all who live to see such times, but that is not for them to decide.
{DIALOGUE}: All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given to us.
{DIALOGUE}: There is a note of finality in Gandalf's voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: There are other forces at work in this world, Frodo, besides the will of evil.
{DIALOGUE}: Bilbo was meant to find the ring.
{DIALOGUE}: In which case, you also were meant to have it...and that is an encouraging thought,
{META_DATA}: (sudden brightness)
{DIALOGUE}: Ah!
{DIALOGUE}: That it's that way!
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf points at the right hand tunnel...the Fellowship scramble to their feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (relieved)
{DIALOGUE}: He's remembered!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: No, but the air doesn't smell so foul down there.
{DIALOGUE}: If in doubt, Meriadoc, always follow your nose!
{META_DATA}: (laughs)
{DIALOGUE}: Ye s..
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 91.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DWAROWDELF CHAMBER, MORIA -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship pass under an arched doorway into a black and empty space.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf pauses...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Let me risk a little more light.
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf taps his staff...for a brief moment a light
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: blazes... like a silent Flash of Lightning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Great shadows spring up and flee...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Behold!
{DIALOGUE}: The great realm and Dwarf city of Dwarrowdelf!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo gasps at the brief sight of a vast roof, far above
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: their heads, upheld by many mighty pillars hewn of stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Before them stretches a huge empty hall, with black walls, polished and smooth as glass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Well, there's an eye opener and no mistake!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ahead of them, a wooden door has been smashed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black arrows are embedded in the timbers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two goblin skeletons lie in the doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli rushes ahead...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Gimli!!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BALIN'S TOMB, MORIA -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli rushes into another vast empty chamber... lit with a narrow shaft of sunlight, beaming in from a small hole near the roof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dwarf and Goblin skeletons are piled high.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the far corner sits a stone walled Well.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shaft of light falls directly onto a stone table in the middle of the room: a single oblong block, about 4 feet high, topped with a great slab of white stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli falls to his knees...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: No...no...oh, no!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli sobs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf quietly reads an inscription of runes, carved onto the white stone slab.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 92.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: "Here lies Balin, son of Fudin, Lord of Moria."
{DIALOGUE}: He is dead, then.
{DIALOGUE}: It's as I had feared.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf carefully lifts the rotting remains of a book from the white stone slab.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has been slashed and stabbed...and appears to be covered in Dried Blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pages crack and break as he opens it...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{META_DATA}: (urgent whisper to Argorn)
{DIALOGUE}: We must move on, we cannot linger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (reading)
{DIALOGUE}: "They have taken the Bridge and the second hall: we have barred the gates...but cannot hold them for long...the ground shakes...drums in the deep...we cannot get out.
{DIALOGUE}: A shadow moves in the dark.
{DIALOGUE}: Will no- one save us?
{DIALOGUE}: They are coming."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unnerved, Pippin backs away nervously...He stumbles against the well, sending a precariously balanced Armored skeleton tumbling in!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry reaches out, Grabbing hold of Pippin before he falls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship freeze in stunned silence as the armored skeleton clatters down the deep well...echoing loudly!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MORIA CAVERNS -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf turns angrily on Pippin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{META_DATA}: (angry)
{DIALOGUE}: Fool of a Took!
{DIALOGUE}: Throw yourself in next time and rid us of your stupidity!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: PIPPIN, CHASTENED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They fall silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A low rolling boom rises from the depths below...growing louder...BOOM...BOOM...as if the caverns of Moria were turned into a vast drum.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A great horn blasts nearby...Answering horns ... running feet...harsh cries... Sam's eyes glance at Frodo's belt...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (worried)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 93.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A cold blue glow is emanating from Sting's Scabbard!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo draws the Sword...and stares at its glowing blade!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: Orcs !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (to the hobbits)
{DIALOGUE}: Get back!
{DIALOGUE}: Stay close to Gandalf.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn and Boromir slam and wedge the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir catches sight of something; he turns to Aragorn with shock in his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: They have a cave troll!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli snatches up two rusty dwarf axes and leaps onto the tomb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (yelling)
{DIALOGUE}: Let them come!
{DIALOGUE}: There is one Dwarf yet in Moria who still draws breath!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Door bursts open in a shower of wood fragments, and 20 Goblins charge into the tomb, followed by a huge cave troll!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli ducks a blow and immediately buries his Axes in 2 Goblin helmets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn and Boromir wade into the mass of Goblins with their swords.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas fires deadly arrows into Goblin throats, desperately trying to Shield the Hobbits!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf is clutching his sword and joins in the battle!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cave troll is sweeping his club at Aragorn...who stumbles backwards...the huge club descends for the killing blow...suddenly, in a flash of steel, Boromir's long sword slices into the Scaly arm of the troll; it rears back, spewing green blood!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam is backing up against a wall...a sword in one hand, a saucepan in the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In desperation he swings wildly at a Goblin with a saucepan!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It keels over...Sam looks surprised.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wallops another Goblin and it too, drops.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I think I'm getting the hang of this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Cave Troll lunges forward, thrusting at Frodo's chest with his spear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn!
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 94.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam screams as Frodo is lifted off his feet by the spear tip and slammed against the wall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (shocked yell)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hobbits go crazy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam slashes at the cave troll's knee, bringing him down...Merry and Pippin jump on him...Legolas fires an arrow...and the cave troll topples, dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn rushes to Frodo's side as he slumps to the floor...Frodo appears to be dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Gandalf, Aragorn, Hobbits looking horrified... Suddenly Frodo coughs...takes a huge breath.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: He's alive!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I'm alright.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not hurt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: You should be dead.
{DIALOGUE}: That spear would've skewered a wild boar!
