{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. LOTHLORIEN HILLTOP -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Haldir leads the Fellowship onto a Hill Top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look with wonderment at the vista spread before them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several miles towards the South, a Large Hill rises out of the woods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Upon the hill rise many mighty Mallorn Trees, taller than any others...Nestled high in the crown of the mallorns is a Beautiful City.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It Gleams in the low rays of the late afternoon sun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: green, gold, and silver.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To the east of Caras Galadhon, the Woods of Lorien run down the pale gleam of Anduin, the great river.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beyond the River, the land appears flat and empty, formless and vague, until far away, it rises again like a dark and dreary wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Sun that lies on Lothlorien has not power to enlighten the shadows that lie beyond.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CELEBORN'S CHAMBER, CARAS GALADHON -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 100.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: THE FELLOWSHIP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: step onto a wide fleet filled with a soft light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The walls are green and silver, the roof gold and in its midst is the trunk of the might Mallorn tree, now tapering toward its crown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Celeborn steps forward to greet the guests.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hair is long and silver, his face grave and beautiful, with no sign of age upon it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to him stands Galadriel, the Lady of the Elves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has hair of deep gold and timeless, unsurpassed beauty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Celeborn looks hard at Aragorn...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CELEBORN
{DIALOGUE}: Eight there are, yet nine there were set out from Rivendell.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me, where is Gandalf, for I much desire to speak with him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks at Galadriel, standing silently beside Celeborn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (softly aloud)
{DIALOGUE}: ...he has fallen into shadow.
{DIALOGUE}: Galadriel looks to Aragorn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The Quest stands upon the edge of a knife.
{DIALOGUE}: Stray but a little and it will fail, to the ruin of all...Yet hope remains while the company is true.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel's eyes settle on Sam.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Do not let your hearts be troubled.
{DIALOGUE}: Go now and rest for you are weary with sorrow and much toil.
{DIALOGUE}: Galadriel's eyes turn to Frodo...her voice fades.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Tonight you will sleep in peace.
{META_DATA}: (whispered v/o)
{DIALOGUE}: Welcome, Frodo of the Shire... CLOSE ON: FRODO looks at GALADRIEL.
{DIALOGUE}: SUDDEN INSERT: GALADRIEL as she is on the other
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: side... Powerful, divine...no longer of this world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a Piercing white light surrounds her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...one who has seen the eye.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 101.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CARAS GALADHON LAWN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli, Legolas, Merry, Pippin, Frodo and Sam are in a pavilion set among the trees near the fountain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They lie on soft couches as Elves leave food and wine for them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOURNFUL SINGING drifts down from the trees above.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{META_DATA}: (sadly)
{DIALOGUE}: A lament for Gandalf...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: What do they say about him?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: I have not the heart to tell you.
{DIALOGUE}: For me, the grief is still too near.
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir is sitting alone...Aragorn approaches him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Take some rest.
{DIALOGUE}: these borders are well protected.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moonlight catches the trace of tears on Boromir's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn kneels down beside him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: I will find no rest here.
{DIALOGUE}: I heard her voice inside my head...she spoke of my father and the fall of Gondor, and she said to me: "Even now, there
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: is hope left.
{DIALOGUE}: But I cannot see it...it is long since we had any hope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: BOROMIR looks at ARAGORN in despair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: My father is a noble man, but his rule is failing and our.
{DIALOGUE}: our people lose faith.
{DIALOGUE}: He looks to me to make things right...and I would do it, I would see the glory of Gondor restored.
{DIALOGUE}: Have you ever seen it, Aragorn?
{DIALOGUE}: The White Tower of Ecthelion, glimmering like a spike of pearl and silver, its banners caught high in the morning breeze...have you ever been called home by the clear ringing of silver trumpets?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: I have seen the white city.
{DIALOGUE}: long ago.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 102.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir feels Aragorn's love for Minas Tirith and takes heart,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: One day our paths will lead us there, and the tower guards shall take up the call "the Lords of Gondor have returned."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn returns Boromir's smile...betraying his disquiet sadness only when Boromir looks away.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LATER....
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship are asleep on their beds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli is snoring loudly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: BARE FEET tread soundlessly across the lawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Frodo's eyes flicker open...as if by instinct.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GALADRIEL, her White dress glowing in the moonlight, glances at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo follows her...as if drawn by an invisible force.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GALADRIELS GLADE, LORTHLORIEN -- NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Upon a low stone pedestal, carved like a branching tree, sits a shallow Silver Basin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel leads Frodo into the small Glade.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Will you look into the mirror?
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo looks with apprehension at the silver basin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (warily)
{DIALOGUE}: What will I see?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel pours water into the basin from a silver jug...a glow rises from the water.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Even the wisest cannot tell for the mirror shows many things...things that were .
{DIALOGUE}: things that are...and some things that have not yet come to pass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo slowly steps up to the pedestal...he peers into the glossy surface.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The night sky is reflected into the water... suddenly a figure takes form...the bowed figure of an old man, clad in white robes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He walks down a long road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo leans closer to the mirror's surface...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 103.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: GANDALF LIFTS HIS HEAD AND LOOKS DIRECTLY AT FRODO!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO gasps, his face lighting up with hope.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (joyous)
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gandalf looks at Frodo with a fierce intensity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo reaches out his hand toward the surface of the mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly the image flares, burning out to white.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The vision shifts...Frodo gasps in horror!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Shire is in ruins!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image suddenly widens to fill the screen...buildings burning...bodies strewn about...Dark Shapes of ORCS looting and destroying...Bag End, billowing in flames!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Party tree is hacked down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo reels back as the mirror seems to grow...the nightmarish image sweeps past his head, engulfing him entirely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: Hobbiton...now an Industrial wasteland!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fields and trees destroyed...replaced with Brick factories belching smoke!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGE: ORCS brutally herd manacled Hobbits into the Factories!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see Sam...Merry... and Rosie Cotton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Soot- stained and sobbing, they disappear into the factory hell- hole!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, the mirror goes dark...and out of the black abyss a single eye grows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO IS FROZEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unable to move or cry out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ring dangles from his neck, inches above the water...not shimmering with curls of steam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fire erupts around the eye... With a Yell, Frodo pushes himself away from the pedestal and collapses on the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Light instantly fades from the mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo comes to his senses...he is shocked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel stands still as a statue, unmoved, untouched by the horror.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: I know what it is you saw...for it is also in my mind.
{DIALOGUE}: It is the future, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: It is what will come to pass if you should fail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel looks at Frodo intensely...Frodo looks down...in his hand he is clutching the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks up at Galadriel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The fellowship is breaking.
{DIALOGUE}: It has already begun.
{DIALOGUE}: He will try to take the ring.
{DIALOGUE}: You know of whom I speak.
{DIALOGUE}: One by one, it will destroy them all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: If you ask it of me, I will give you the One Ring.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 104.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: You offer it to me freely...I do not deny that my heart has greatly desired this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel suddenly seems to rise in stature before Frodo's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is suddenly afraid of her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: In place of the Dark Lord, you would have a Queen, not dark, but beautiful and terrible as the Dawn.
{DIALOGUE}: Treacherous as the Sea!
{DIALOGUE}: Stronger than the foundations of the earth...all shall love me and despair!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo takes a step away from Galadriel...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel suddenly laughs...a slender Elf-woman once more, clad in simple white, her voice soft and sad.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (gently)
{DIALOGUE}: I pass the test.
{META_DATA}: (laughs)
{DIALOGUE}: I will diminish and go into the west and remain Galadriel.
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo's confidence drains away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I cannot do this alone...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: You are the ring-bearer, Frodo...to bear a ring of power is to be alone.
{DIALOGUE}: This task was appointed to you, and if you do not find a way, no one will.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo realizes what her message is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Then I know what I must do.
{DIALOGUE}: It's just...I'm afraid to do it.
{DIALOGUE}: Galadriel kneels down to Frodo's height, staring at him intently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Even the smallest person can change the course of the future.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ring lies in the palm of Frodo's hand...his fingers close over it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 105.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ORTHANC CHAMBER -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Naked, Lurtz's eyes follow Saruman, alight with a mean intelligence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: They were Elves once.
{DIALOGUE}: Taken by the Dark Powers ... tortured and mutilated...a ruined and terrible form of life.
{DIALOGUE}: And now...perfected.
{DIALOGUE}: My fighting Uruk-Hai.
{DIALOGUE}: Whom do you serve?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LURTZ
{META_DATA}: (gutteral rasp)
{DIALOGUE}: Saruman.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAVERNS BELOW ISENGARD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK CUTS: LURTZ is quickly armored...Breastplate...Leg guards, Helmet...a sword is thrust in Lurtz's hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The URUK- HAI are smearing themselves in white paint...a creepy ritualistic ceremony...the white hand of Isengard is smeared on bodies, faces, and armor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SARUMAN address a crowd of 200 fully armed URUK-HAI.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Hunt them down.
{DIALOGUE}: Do not stop until they are found.
{DIALOGUE}: You do not know pain.
{DIALOGUE}: You do not know fear.
{DIALOGUE}: You will taste man-flesh.
{DIALOGUE}: Saruman turns to Lurtz.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARUMAN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (coldly)
{DIALOGUE}: One of the Halflings carries something of great value...bring him to me...alive and unspoiled...kill the others.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ISENGARD -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lurtz is leading 200 URUK-HAI out of Isengard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: they run fast, their powerful legs carrying them at speed.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SILVERLODE RIVER BANK--DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Fellowship are in small elven boats.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They row away from the Lothlorien Shore into the Silverlode river.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elves quietly watch them depart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Galadriel gives Frodo a small Crystal Phial.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL
{DIALOGUE}: Farewell, Frodo Baggins.
{DIALOGUE}: I give you the light of Earendil, our most beloved star.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 106.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the Fellowship's boats drift past, Galadriel stands alone, watching from the banks of the river.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In his head, Frodo still hears her voice...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GALADRIEL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: May it be a light for you in dark places, when all other lights go out.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVER ANDUIN -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boats pass into the great river Anduin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Three Elven boats carry the Fellowship steadily southward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Green trees slowly give way to a brown and withered land.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FOREST -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Uruk forces are running through the trees with deadly purpose.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. RIVER ANDUIN -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A flock of birds circle high above, Black against the pale sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn watches them with concern.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PILLARS OF THE KINGS, RIVER ANDUIN--DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Three Elven boats drift slowly through the steep rocky gorge in the Pre-dawn light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ARAGORN, slowly paddling in the stern.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo slowly looks up, his eyes widening with amazement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: Two enormous rock statues, towering like 300 foot pinnacles on either side of the river...carved images of Gondorian kings of old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They loom over the boats with power and majesty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The Argonath...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Aragorn...strangely moved by the beauty of the silent sentinels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He speaks, almost as if to himself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (deeply moved)
{DIALOGUE}: Long have I desired to look upon the kings of old...my kin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fellowship stare in stunned silence as the current takes them through the narrow gap between the Statues' feet.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 107.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wide on: Craning up past the statues vast crumbling heads, to reveal a large lake only a mile down river...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SHORE OF NEN HITHOEL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: THE FELLOWSHIP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they leap out of the boats and clamber onto the wooded shore.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: We cross the lake at nightfall, hide the boats and continue on foot.
{DIALOGUE}: we approach Mordor from the North.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (gloomy)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yes, just a simple matter of finding our way through Emyn Muil, an impassable labyrinth of razor sharp rocks.
{DIALOGUE}: And after that gets even better...a festering, stinking marshland, far as the eye can see.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: That is our Road...I suggest you take some rest and recover your strength, Master Dwarf.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{META_DATA}: (indignant)
{DIALOGUE}: Recover my...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas turns to Aragorn with urgency.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: We should leave now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: Orcs patrol the Eastern shore.
{DIALOGUE}: We must wait for cover of darkness.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: It is not the Eastern shore that worries me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas casts a glance around into the Parth Galen forest...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: A shadow and a threat has been growing in my mind.
{DIALOGUE}: Something draws near, I can feel it.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 108.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn looks at Legolas, knowing full well what he means.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam has slumped asleep...Merry dumps a small pile of kindling at Gimli's feet...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Where's Frodo?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam sits up with a start...Aragorn's head snaps round.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: his eyes fly to Boromir's shield which lies abandoned by his camp bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ARAGORN....
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as he realizes Boromir has gone!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SLOPES OF AMON HEN -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is walking beneath the trees...lost in thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His feet hit the rough edge of an ancient stone slab...his eyes follow an overgrown path towards stone stairs leading to the summit of Amon Hen...the seeing seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CRACKLING SOUND!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo freezes....
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: None of us should wander alone; you least of all.
{DIALOGUE}: So much depends on you...Frodo?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo turns slowly...he stares at Boromir, tense, cautious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I know why you seek solitude.
{DIALOGUE}: You suffer, I see it day by day.
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure you do not suffer needlessly?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo stands silent for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the murmur of the Wind in the trees and the distant roar of the falls of Rauros can be heard
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Let me help you.
{DIALOGUE}: There are other ways, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: other paths that we might take.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I know what you would say, and it would seem like wisdom but for the warning of my heart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Warning?
{DIALOGUE}: Against what?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir has started forward towards Frodo, he pulls himself up.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 109.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: We are all afraid, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: But to let that fear drive us to destroy what hope we have...don't you see that is madness?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: There is no other way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: I ask only for the strength to defend my people.
{META_DATA}: (angrily drops the wood he has collected)
{DIALOGUE}: If you would but lend me the ring...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: No. . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo steps hurriedly away from Boromir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you recoil?
{DIALOGUE}: I am no thief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (wary)
{DIALOGUE}: You are not yourself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: What chance do you think you have?
{DIALOGUE}: They will find you, they will take the ring and you will beg for death before the end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo turns to leave.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You fool!
{DIALOGUE}: It is not yours save by unhappy chance...it might have been mine.
{DIALOGUE}: It should be mine.
{DIALOGUE}: Give it to me!
{DIALOGUE}: Give me the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir leaps on top of Frodo, grasping for the ring!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo has only moments to act.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo rips the ring from around his neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: and rams it on his finger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO DISAPPEARS
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir spins wildly around, yelling into thin air!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: I see your mind...you will take the ring to Sauron.
{DIALOGUE}: You will betray us!
{DIALOGUE}: You go to your death and the death of us all.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 110.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Curse you!
{DIALOGUE}: Curse you and your Halflings!
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir stumbles and falls.
{DIALOGUE}: His body shakes as if in the Throes of a fit...slowly he comes to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (Disoriented)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: What have I done.
{DIALOGUE}: Please, Frodo...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SEEING SEAT -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE TWILIGHT WORLD:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO races through the misty twilight world, past the foggy shapes of twisted trees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Somewhere behind him, Boromir's distraught voice carries from another dimension:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, Frodo...Frodo...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo suddenly finds himself on the stone steps...he clambers up the stairs, onto a high seat, perched on four stone pillars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo cowers on the seat, like a lost child upon the throne of mountain kings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The world of mist swirls around him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo peers out from the seat...the world seems to shrink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In all directions, Views of far off lands telescope towards him through the mist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGES: ORCS spilling out of holes in the misty mountains... flames rising from Mirkwood...grim faced easterlings march to war...black ships sailing into the south.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All the power of the Dark Lord is in motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo moves his gaze towards the east...fire explodes against the smoke, as a huge mass of black battlements fills Frodo's vision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A mountain of iron, immeasurably strong, tower of adamant: Barad-dur, FORTRESS OF SAURON!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAURON'S EYE LEAPS TOWARD FRODO LIKE A FINGER OF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIGHT.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAURON (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (IN BLACK SPEECH)
{DIALOGUE}: They will fall!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo leaps off the seat, and tumbles down the stairs!
{DIALOGUE}: The eye sweeps Amon Hen like a searchlight, seeking its ring!
{DIALOGUE}: With a huge effort, Frodo wrenches the ring off his finger...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SUMMIT OF AMON HEN -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo lies gasping on the summit of Amon Hen...below the ancient ruins of the seeing seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 111.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THAT MOMENT: A BLACK BOOT STEPS INTO SHOT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks up as Aragorn towers over him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (numb)
{DIALOGUE}: It has taken Boromir.
{DIALOGUE}: ARAGORN moves towards Frodo...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (urgent)
{DIALOGUE}: Where is the ring?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo backs away from Aragorn...Aragorn is shocked by the movement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Stay away!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo...I swore to protect you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Can you protect me from yourself?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo uncurls his fist...in is palm lies the ring!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It glints, gold and beautiful in the afternoon sun...Aragorn's eyes are drawn to it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Would you destroy it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (kneeling to Frodo)
{DIALOGUE}: I would have gone with you to the end... into the very fires of Mordor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: I know...Look after the others, especially Sam...he will not understand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn freezes!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He draws his sword.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{META_DATA}: (urgent)
{DIALOGUE}: Go, Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo hesitates.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 112.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (yells)
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{DIALOGUE}: Run!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo backs away into the trees...as 200 URUK-HAI SWARM onto Amon Hen behind Aragorn!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn attacks the leading URUK-HAI like a madman... he brings two down with his sword...leaping into the ruins as others close in on him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo scrambles down the hillside, away from the fight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn battles the URUK-HAI, amongst the pillars and blocks of Amon Hen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Despite his bravery, he is quickly surrounded... SUDDENLY: ELVEN ARROWS smash into the URUK-HAI.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas races out of the woods, firing his bow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gimli leaps into the battle, wielding his might axe.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PARTH GALEN HILLSIDE -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo is darting down the steep hillside as heave feet thunder down behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks around for Frodo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: LURTZ ordering his URUKS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LURTZ
{DIALOGUE}: Find the Halflings ... find the halflings!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo stumbles and falls...quickly he crawls behind a tree...above him the sound of Uruk-Hai crashing through the forest rings out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (O.S.)
{META_DATA}: (urgent whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo turns to see Merry and Pippin hidden in a hollow, a few feet away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Hide here, quick!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Come on...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo looks at his friends... slowly shakes his head, a great sadness in his eyes...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: What's he doing?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 113.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry's eyes meet Frodo's.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Understanding.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: He's leaving.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pippin stands and makes a move toward Frodo...Merry grabs at his arm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY
{DIALOGUE}: Pippin!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE ECHO OF BOROMIR'S HORN reaches Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli...they are battling their way down the Slopes towards the lake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: The horn of Gondor!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn desperately slashes his way towards Boromir, felling URUK-HAI in his path...while Legolas and Gimli fight a rear guard action.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MANY URUK-HAI fall to Boromir's sword as he tries to protect Merry and Pippin...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lurtz takes aim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A black arrow suddenly thuds into Boromir's chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Amazingly, Boromir continues fighting, but another arrow...and another, brings him to his knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Merry and Pippin are scooped off their feet by URUK-HAI.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MERRY & PIPPIN
{DIALOGUE}: Aaaaagh!
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir!
{DIALOGUE}: Boromir!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lurtz aims his bow at Boromir's heart... suddenly Aragorn charges at him, smashing the Bow with his sword.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They lock into a deadly battle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn cuts Lurtz down and races towards Boromir, who lies slumped against a tree...URUK-HAI arrows sticking out of his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At least 20 dead URUK-HAI lie heaped around Boromir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His horn lies at his feet...Cloven in two.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{META_DATA}: (painful gasp)
{DIALOGUE}: They took the little ones...
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 114.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn quickly tries to staunch the flow of Blood from Boromir's shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (panicked)
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo...where is Frodo?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: I let Frodo go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir holds Aragorn's gaze.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Then you did what I could not.
{DIALOGUE}: I tried to take the ring from him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: The ring is beyond our reach now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Forgive me, I did not see.
{DIALOGUE}: I have failed you all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: No, Boromir.
{DIALOGUE}: You fought bravely.
{DIALOGUE}: You have kept your honor.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn tries to bind Boromir's wound.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Leave it!
{DIALOGUE}: It is over...the world of Men will fall and all will come to darkness and my city to ruin.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: I do not know what strength is in my blood, but I swear to you... I will not let the White City fall, nor your people fail...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR
{DIALOGUE}: Our people...our people...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn places Boromir's sword in his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boromir's fingers tighten around the hilt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOROMIR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I would have followed you, my brother...my captain, my King.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn lays Boromir down.
{DIALOGUE}: He is dead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Be at peace, son of Gondor.
{DIALOGUE}: Aragorn bends and Kisses Boromir's forehead.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 115.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (3)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Legolas and Gimli appear behind him...Aragorn stands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: They will look for his coming from the white tower...but he will not return.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SHORE OF NEN HITHOEL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the lakeshore Frodo stands in front of one of the Elvish Boats, the ring in his palm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A distraught Sam...running as hard as he can through the forest...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo looks to the far side of the river...the camera moves in on the ring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I wish the ring had never come to me.
{DIALOGUE}: I wish none of this had happened...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears fall down Frodo's face...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: So do all who lie to see such times...but that is not for them to decide.
{DIALOGUE}: All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With renewed determination, Frodo tucks the ring inside his vest pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The small figure of Frodo pushing the Elvish boat into the water... Sam bursts through the trees and runs toward the lake...Frodo is already paddling away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (anguished)
{DIALOGUE}: Not alone, Frodo.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Frodo!
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo, in the boat, paddling steadfastly away from the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: shore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: tears in his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the voice of Sam carried on the wind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo whispers to himself
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: No, Sam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam looks at the water...then at the boat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SPLASH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO turns to see Sam launching himself into the water.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 116.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Go back,Sam.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to Mordor alone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam splashes hopelessly toward the boat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Of course you are...and I'm coming with you!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: You can't swim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam starts to go under, spluttering and coughing...Frodo drops his paddle and scrambles backwards in the boat...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (frightened)
{DIALOGUE}: Sam!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sam is underwater...hands flailing helplessly as he sinks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on: Frodo's hand grasping Sam's... Frodo pulls a bedraggled and half drowned Sam into the boat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo and Sam look at each other, out of breath, tears and water streaming down both their faces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: I made a promise, Mr. Frodo...a promise.
{META_DATA}: (fierce passion)
{DIALOGUE}: "Don't you leave him, Samwise Gamgee."
{META_DATA}: (sobs)
{DIALOGUE}: And I don't mean to...I don't mean to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (crying)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, Sam!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo starts to laugh through his tears...the two friends hug.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Come on then.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two Hobbits row through the water...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FALLS OF RAUROS AERIAL -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slow motion: Looking down on swiftly flowing water...Boromir's body slides under camera.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is lying in one of the boats, his arms across his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: his broken horn at his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly... the boat drops away from camera...as it plunges over the massive falls of Rauros, disappearing into the vapor below.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 117.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: If we are quick, we will catch Frodo and Sam before nightfall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn looks towards the far shore; Frodo and Sam's small Boat can be seen lying on the distant Riverbank as Frodo and Sam make off into the forest beyond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't react.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legolas turns and looks at Aragorn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You mean not to follow them...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
