{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: Not if we hold true to each other.
{DIALOGUE}: We will not abandon Merry and Pippin to torment and death, not while we have strength left.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn pulls a HUNTING KNIFE out of his pack and straps it on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Leave all that can be spared behind... CLOSE ON: ARAGORN.
{DIALOGUE}: a steely light in his eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (grimly)
{DIALOGUE}: We travel light.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's hunt some Orc.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: Yes!
{DIALOGUE}: Ha!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli disappear into the Woods, following the URUK-HAI trail.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. EMYN MUIL HILLTOP -- DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frodo and Sam scramble onto a high ridge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A distant line of Saw toothed mountains below a dark, oppressive sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black volcanic smoke rises behind the mountains....MORDOR!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 118.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
